neighborhood_overview:
Staying in the 9th arrondissement, you will be in the heart of one of the capital's liveliest neighborhoods. Numerous designer boutiques, restaurants, bars, cafés, entertainment... are all within walking distance. You can also walk to the Moulin Rouge, the Montorgueil district, Montmartre or even Notre-Dame. You will only need to take the metro to discover the historic centre of Paris, the Père-Lachaise cemetery, the Place de la Bastille, but also the Champs-Elysées, the Eiffel Tower and all the great monuments that make Paris the most beautiful city in the world.

neighborhood_overview:
Close to the Canal de l'Ourcq, the apartment is locate in the neighborhood è situato nel quartiere La Villette, a new and dynamic area in the city. The subway line 7 (Crimée) or the RER E (Rosa Parks) will easily take you to the city center, but you will get to Place de la République only in a 20 minutes walk.
Every summer Paris Plage (Paris Beach) is organized on the canal, and the Parc de la Villette organize a cinema under the stars (and many other activities).
You can visit the cité des sciences, cité de la musique and the new opera theater, the art and cultural center 104.
Cruises on the canal are regularly organized, a different way to discover Paris.
The neighborhood is a typical area for families, with movie theaters and shop nearby (Decathlon, Castorama, Leroy Merlin, ecc...).
Don't miss the chance to have a drink or eat in one of the many bars on the canal.

description:
Deco's Place Teodora è uno splendido appartamento situato al terzo piano di uno stabile residenziale nel quartiere Celio,a due passi dal Colosseo.
Completamente ristrutturato,l'appartamento è dotato di ogni comfort ed è l'ideale per le famiglie o coppie di amici che vogliono soggiornare e vivere Roma come se fossero cittadini Romani.
L'appartamento dista circa 200m dalla stazione della metro Colosseo e percorrendo Via dei Fori Imperiali a piedi è possibile raggiungere Piazza Venezia in 15 minuti

The space
É composto da un ampio ingresso, due camere da letto con bagno privato, un salotto con divano letto e bagno, un bagno di servizio e una cucina con balcone arredato. Ogni stanza è dotata di aria condizionata ed è possibile usufruire di elettrodomestici quali lavatrice, ferro da stiro, lavastoviglie, forno, forno a microonde, macchina del caffè e tv.

License number
QA/2020/32644
neighborhood_overview:
Teodora è immersa nel Rione Celio, un quartiere ricco di storia, caratterizzato dalla presenza di tre chiese importanti quali la Basilica di San Clemente, la Chiesa di San Giovanni e Paolo al Celio e la Basilica dei Santi Quattro Coronati, oggi sede di un convento di suore di clausura.
Passeggiando per il quartiere ci si imbatte nel Clivio di Scauro, un'antica strada romana con archi medievali che solcano la via; Villa Celimontana, un parco pubblico risalente al Cinquecento, oggi scenario di diversi eventi culturali.
Il Rione ha mantenuto la sua identità e unicità grazie anche alla presenza di numerosi ristoranti tipici romani, enoteche, bar e pub e anche alla presenza del mercato rionale di frutta e verdura .

Welcome to Feels Like Home S. Bento Cozy Flat IV!

This lovely duplex located just a few minutes from downtown is the ideal choice for your next city break. On the upper floor, you have a spacious bedroom with a comfortable double bed and a bathroom with a shower. Downstairs, you have a well-equipped kitchenette, one toilet and a bright living room with sofa and a private terrace to enjoy the sunny days.

Nearby, you can find the Bairro Alto, the nightlife heart of the city where you will find fado houses, trendy bars, and many restaurants.
The Rato subway station is just 10 minutes away and it will allow you to get to any point in the city. You can also opt for taking the light rail route 28 that goes through many of the most important and old Lisbon neighborhoods. You will find an urban qualified space that is perfect for the challenges of modern life with its varied architectural expression.

neighborhood_overview: The vibrant area of Testaccio is a gourmet heaven, renowned for its food culture, with a great number of restaurants, coffee bars, gelaterie, wine bars, and the best food market in Rome. neighborhood_overview:
Sintra is one of those places full of magic and mystery where nature and man combined in such a perfect symbiosis, that UNESCO classified it as a World Heritage. We can find in the village of Sintra testimonies from practically all periods of Portuguese history and you will see the largest number of castles and palaces in one region, many of them looking like they came out of fairy tales. You also find a wide variety of restaurants and cafés within walking distance of the property. Sintra is particularly known for the Queijadas de Sintra and Travesseiros, delicacies that can be sampled in several nearby pastry shops.
Other than that, the local views are breathtaking.

Among the various local attractions, the main tourist attractions of Sintra are:
- Palácio Nacional de Sintra
- Castelo dos Mouros
- Quinta da Regaleira
- Palácio de Seteais
- Palácio de Monserrate

neighborhood_overview:
Kypseli used to be the upscale neighborhood of Athens, which had in its premises many art galleries, historic cafés and restaurants, as well as the houses of some of the most prominent families in the city. It was the Upper East Side of Athens and now it is coming alive again.

After the 80’s the demographics changed and Kypseli kept its vintage character, its nice people and cute little cafés.

While walking during the daytime you can meet a variety of people, from businessmen to students, from refugees to artists. It is truly a diverse neighborhood.

neighborhood_overview:
Die Unterkünfte liegen im Bezirk Neukölln mitten im 1737 gegründeten historischen Arbeiterviertel Böhmisch-Rixdorf. In unmittelbarer Umgebung: Cafés, Bars, Einkaufsmöglichkeiten, Neuköllner Oper, Kinos, zahlreiche Galerien, Volkspark Hasenheide und Tempelhofer Feld.
In Berlin bieten sich zahlreiche Möglichkeiten, historische und moderne Kultur besuchen, sich zu erholen, das Zusammenwachsen von Ost und West intensiv und lebendig erleben. Besondere Anziehungspunkten sind der historische Stadtkern mit dem Brandenburger Tor und der Straße unter den Linden sowie dem angrenzenden Regierungsviertel, einzigartige Museen, eine traditionsreiche Industriekultur, moderne Architektur oder die städtischen Naherholungsgebiete.
Auf Wunsch gestalten wir Stadtführungen mit sachkundigen Stadtführern. Hierzu beraten wir Sie gern. Für Gruppen bis 8 Personen bieten wir Führungen für 20 Euro an, jede weitere Person 2 Euro. Die Nutzung des Berliner Nahverkehrs kostet extra.

The space
Welcome!

Just in front of the Ajuda Botanical Gardens, this private suite is situated in the basement level of a neoclassical building which has all of its original beauty and features preserved, but has all the modern comforts and necessities needed for a comfortable stay, especially when situated in one of the more quiet areas of Lisbon that isn't frequented by lots of tourists -- an extreme rarity in the city!

As you step inside, you'll be greeted by a
neighborhood_overview:
Ajuda is a hillside residential neighborhood overlooking the Tagus River. The vast, neoclassical Ajuda National Palace draws visitors with its opulent, period interiors. Views from the neighboring 18th-century botanical garden take in the 25 de Abril Bridge and the Christ the King monument across the river. Monsanto Forest Park has popular trails for jogging and bicycling, as well as a busy playground.

As one of the less-touristy areas, Ajuda is a tranquil neighbourhood - perfect for those who don't enjoy large crowds or loud noises found in nearby neighbourhoods of Belém and Alcântara - which is a rarity to find in this part of Lisbon. Furthermore, it's connected to Monsanto, which is a fantastic area for jogging and walking, and there is also some outdoor callisthenics equipment like pull-up bars located in the park.

description:
An apartment of 130 sqm right in the heart of East Berlin, located next to the beloved park of Prenzlauer Berg, Mauer Park.

The space
Consisting of two big bedrooms, a kitchen, a huge lounge, two bathrooms with bathtube and shower, the apartment can welcome 4 persons. The apartment is on the 4th floor with elevator.

Since 2014, the tourists in Berlin have to pay a city tax (5% from the rent) so I will ask you to pay this tax in cash the day you will arrive.

The kitchen has all what you need: dishwash
neighborhood_overview:
Prenzlauer Berg is no doubt one of the most mythical districts of the city.
It embodies Berlin’s cultural heritage from diverse historical periods, proletarian and middle-class styles of the fin-de-siècle, just as the imprint of socialism.
What is more, there has always been a tradition of resistance and opposition giving birth to the spirit of creativity that incessantly surrounds you here.
The architecture should hold attention because in spite of the galloping renovation since the fall of the Wall, it still retains some of scars from the Second World War.

We are also in walking distance to Hoxton and Shoreditch, which is well known for its amazing nightlife. The area is fashionable and has lots of restaurants, cool bars and on trend shops.

There are two local supermarkets open until at least 11pm.

neighborhood_overview:
Mouraria is, without a doubt, one of the most traditional and multicultural neighborhoods in Lisbon. After all, it was here that the Moors came to live after D. Afonso Henriques conquered Lisbon in 1147, until they were finally expelled from Portuguese territory four centuries later.
Today, more than six centuries later, this beautiful part of the Portuguese capital continues to be the choice of more than 50 different nationalities, with the majority coming from China, India, Bangladesh, Pakistan, and Mozambique, just to name a few of the largest communities in this neighborhood.
Mouraria still is a typical Lisbon neighborhood, with its own characteristics, its own traditions and customs, and especially its unique people.

People spill into the street from the Gare du Nord, one of the busiest rail terminals in the world, and mingle into a melting pot of old Paris, new Paris, and cultural offerings from around the world.
I's where you find two of the last covered markets in Paris as the Marché St Quentin.

Alfama is one of Lisbon’s most typical and old neighbourhoods. It goes from the São Jorge’s castle until the Tagus River. It’s distinguished by its narrow streets, populated by small buildings, churches, nooks and small squares that survived the 1755 earthquake.
In this neighbourhood where modernity and tradition coexist, there are several belvederes with the most amazing views over Lisbon and the Tagus River. In almost every corner the Fado can be heard and seen. There are many restaurants serving delicious traditional food. To dive into Lisbon’s history, the São Jorge’s castle, the cathedrals, the monasteries, the chapels and the various ruins should be visited. Culture is also very present through the museums, the live-music pubs, the art galleries, the theatres and the book shops that you can go to.

En el Raval confluyen edificaciones históricas, tales como la iglesia románica de San Pablo del Campo, la iglesia de Sant Agustí o el mercado de La Boquería, junto con edificaciones modernas, destinadas a la cultura y el esparcimiento, como por ejemplo el Museo de Arte Contemporáneo de Barcelona (MACBA) o el Centro de Cultura Contemporánea de Barcelona.

neighborhood_overview: The Marais district gets its name from its location: once a marshland (‘marais’), it has been inhabited ever since it was drained back in the 12th century. This historic area is now one of the most visited districts of the French capital, for its architectural heritage as well as its unique vibe. The district is shaped like a triangle, bordered respectively by Place de la Bastille, Place de la République and the Hôtel de Ville. It has a number of private mansions dating to the 17th and 18th centuries, some of which have been converted into internationally renowned museums such as the Musée Picasso, the Maison de Victor Hugo and the Musée Carnavalet. The beautiful and well-proportioned square known as Place des Vosges is a highlight of a stroll through the Marais. Rue des Rosiers, the Jewish quarter of Paris, is well worth exploring for its old-world atmosphere and its offbeat shops and restaurants. The Marais has any number of trendy shops and restaurants, as well as its own department

Just a 2 minute walk from the Phoenix Park, welcome to your cosy home away from home in Dublin. This 1890s built cottage from the Victorian era is awaiting your arrival.

Stoneybatter was named by TimeOut’s as one of the world’s ‘trendiest’ neighbourhoods. This cottage is ideally located with just a 7min walk to some of Dublin's best cafés, restaurants and bars.

We’re also just a 15 min drive, 20 min public transport, 13 min cycle or 35 min walk from Dublin City Centre.

The space

Phoenix Park is Europe’s biggest urban park with endless sprawling greenery to cycle, walk and explore that's just two minutes from our door.

Once a small fisherman village Cascais developed into a popular holiday destination over the past few decades featuring a charming old town and some of the best beaches in the area. In this guide I introduce you to the must visits and best things to do in Cascais, Portugal.

Cascais is a coastal city, located just a 30 minute drive away from Lisbon. Ever since it has been the place where Portuguese royalty would spend their summer holiday and with that attract many members of Portuguese nobility over time.
This isn’t a tropical land, but you’re not far from that warm, nice feeling. You get to wear sleeveless shirts even in spring and autumn. It helps that beaches form a spine of sorts for Cascais, and that the average number of sunny days per year is around 300 (yes, you read that right). Thus, even in the coldest months, the waters are full of surfers, the beaches are full of athletes and the Cascais “paredão” is full of people strolling.

neighborhood_overview:
The North side of amsterdam is upcoming since a few years. Untill 5 years ago, the place seemed a bit dull, and people from the city centre hardly ever took the ferry to have a look here. Houses were cheap, and therefore a lot of creatives and artists started to move here. Since then the 'jump over the IJ river' has been made and now it is one of the hottest area's in town. Even the new York times wrote about it as one of the world's top 10 hip places in the world.
The area still feels like a village: human scale housing, a lot of green and parks (it is the greenest area in Amsterdam).
The van der Pekbuurt is also still one of the poorest area's in Amsterdam. And a lot of other area's in the North are. But it is getting mixed now, and the mix is a nice one.

neighborhood_overview:
Tooting has been listed in the Top 10 coolest neighbourhoods in the world (!) by Lonely Planet travel guide:
"Tooting has developed into an uber-cool neighbourhood and lost none of its gritty charm in the process. Rubbing shoulders with perfectly pleasant yet slightly square Wimbledon, Earlsfield and Balham, Tooting is a more captivating affair, revelling in multiculturalism and originality.

Its high street which stretches between two Tube stations, is one of the best ‘curry corridors’ in the country, and contains some superb South Asian restaurants, like Dosa n Chutny and Apollo Banana Leaf.
The best shopping can be found inside eclectic Tooting Market, and quirky bars and pubs include The Castle, The Antelope and The Little Bar. The Tooting Commons create over 200 acres of green space between them, and are home to Tooting Bec Lido – the largest swimming pool in the United Kingdom".

name: Townhouse in London · ★4.76 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1.5 baths
description:
Large two bed maisonette in Islington

Within walking distance of Stoke Newington and Dalston and also a short stroll through Highbury fields to Upper Street.

Easy and fast connections to Central London and great views over London!

Also, I'm an old school Airbnb sort which means this is my home and is available only when I'm not in town. It's not a rental flat & has art, plants, music and comfort galore.

The space
Lovely, light, stylish and large Islington flat within easy reach of the hustle of Stoke Newington and Dalston; or the bustle of Upper Street and Clerkenwell.

In spite of that it's in a very quiet spot in a cul de sac; and with some great little shops a stone's throw away.

There are two double bedrooms with super comfortable beds; the kitchen is brand new; there are two balconies; the main bathroom has a large shower, and a separate bath; there's a separate toilet with washing machine and there's a
neighborhood_overview:
A great location in historic Islington, one of London's more upmarket districts, with easy access to the nightlife of east London and the sights of West London.

The flat is between Highbury Fields, a quite posh park with tennis courts (you might recognise the opening and closing scenes from Four Weddings and A Funeral); and Clissold Park, which is larger and great for jogging, tennis, people watching, feeding the goats or a combination of those.

Nearby Upper Street has more bars and restaurants than any other street in the UK plus a variety of boutiques and high street shopping.

Highbury is a foodies paradise with an amazing array of small shops on the doorstep catering for those who love to cook. And some of London's favourite restaurants are just around the corner.

Plus getting around is simple: the local underground is one stop away from Kings Cross / St Pancras station

The space
Questa suite adatta a 1-4 persone è completamente indipendente ed ha tutte le comodità: letto matrimoniale, un letto divano (Ikea) comodo per 1-2 adulti, a richiesta abbiamo la culla. Cabina armadio, tavolo 4 posti. Frigo in camera, bollitore da te, macchina caffè espresso (Lavazza), microonde, etc. WiFi, TV. Asciugacapelli, acqua calda, ampio bagno privato con doccia e bidè. neighborhood_overview: Il quartiere Trieste è molto bello da vivere, lo definirei il salotto della città per la tranquillità e lo stile di vita dei suoi residenti. Spesso il caos e la frenesia non danno tempo di dedicarsi a se stessi e anche il luogo dove si vive ci comprime in una corsa verso casa. Qui è diverso: il facile collegamento metro B1 si affaccia sulla bella piazza Annibaliano, luogo di incontro e passeggio per i piccoli bimbi, una cornice storica si staglia ai confine della piazza con il complesso monumentale di Santa Agnese fuori le mura e il mausoleo di Santa Costanza, luogo di indubbio interesse culturale da visitare; risalente ai primi anni del cristianesimo conserva ancora le catacombe. Nei dintorni viali e piccole vie o slarghi offrono spazio a bistrot, enoteche e ristoranti; street food, Caffé e gelaterie d'eccezione dove studenti della blasonata università Luiss amano trascorrere il tempo libero conversando. Il corso Trieste è proprio una chicca.

description:
Our architect-designed family home sleeps 4 (+2 on futon) in 3 lovely bedrooms. We're located in trendy, stylish Crouch End, 2 mins walk from great shops & cafes, and 30mins from central London.

The space
We built our home ourselves a few years ago and really love it. It is built in around a courtyard so it's very light and airy, especially in the summer when you can open up all the glass doors onto the courtyard.

The courtyard is perfect place for sitting out and soaking up the sunshine. Everything in the house is brand-new except our furniture which is a mix of retro and contemporary.

On the ground floor, each room has a wall of glass looking out onto the courtyard.

- master bedroom with en-suite wet room, with toilet, sink and shower

- study

Downstairs there are:
- 2 bedrooms -
neighborhood_overview:
Crouch End is very stylish and bohemian part of London. It's full of excellent independent cafes, restaurants and boutique shops, as well as not one but two art house cinemas. There’s also supermarkets, butchers, bakeries and green grocers for any fresh produce you may want.
There’s a leisure complex with gym and indoor and outdoor swimming pools a few minutes’ walk away, as well as parks on the doorstep.

We're close to Highgate Woods and Hampstead Heath for walks, and lovely 'villagey' neighbourhoods of Hampstead, Highgate and Muswell Hill are nearby. Everywhere in London is easily accessible - there's no tube but it only takes 10 minutes by (very frequent) bus to get to Finsbury Park Station, in zone 2. You can be in central London in 25 minutes.

We love it round here and can't imagine living anywhere else!

There are many cafes, restaurants and shops on our doorstep. It is a 3 minute walk to the train station with direct trains to London Waterloo in 30 minutes. 10 minute walk to Richmond.

A large, recently renovated 3 storey Victorian house.

neighborhood_overview:
Things to do in the local area

St Margarets is a village between Richmond and Twickenham and has excellent transport links into London from its overground railway (4-5 minute walk).

There are plenty of shops, cafes, pubs and restaurants here and in the surrounding area.

Childrens’ activities:
- There are good swing parks in Moormead Park and Marble Hill Park, next to the river.
- Swimming at Pools on the Park is a 4 minute drive away.
- Snakes and Ladders in Syon Park is a good ‘softplay’ and is about 10 minutes by car.
- Hampton Court Palace with it’s Magic Garden make for a fantastic family day out.

Marble Hill Park is a 5 minute walk away and is great for jogging, tiring out children, or taking a quiet walk through and down to the River Thames. If you turn left at the river you will reach Richmond Bridge; turn right and you will end up in Twickenham.

name: Home in London · ★4.84 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath
description:
Welcome to our stunning house with garden in Battersea where you will feel comfortably at home and experience the city like a local.

The space
The house is a 1970s style terraced house in a safe area which is close (walkable in five minutes) to shops (supermarkets, launderette, French, Indian, Thai, Italian, Persian, Pizza, Argentinian and other restaurants, coffee bars and craft-beer pub).

It doesn't look much from the outside, but we have put a lot of thought and love into the inside - and we love the result. The real beauty about our house is its location - a ten-minute walk to both Clapham Common (tube - Northern Line) or Clapham Junction (mainline trains). There are buses direct to the west end, Vauxhall, Westminster, Waterloo, Soho, Chelsea and Victoria. Outside the congestion charge zone, parking is possible outside, but you have to pay and get a ticket from a machine nearby. Parking is free at weekends. During the week the restrictions are 9.
neighborhood_overview:
A mixed residential area behind two main north/south and east/west roads. Quiet (mostly) and very central (you can be in Westminster/West End/Victoria in 20 mins by bus, or 15 mins by Uber). Very close to Clapham Common (Northern Line Tube) and Clapham Junction (mainline train).

The area is slowly gentrifying, so we now have a "hip" new independent coffee bar two minutes walk away, our favourite French restaurant less than a minute away, two other French restaurants three minutes and ten minutes away respectively, Indian, Thai, Italian, Chinese, and Argentinian restaurants all locally - and buses into Soho, Chelsea and the Kings Road just outside.

There is on-road parking outside which usually has free spaces, but you will need to buy permits in advance as the ticket machine will only issue tickets for 4 hours maximum.

name: Sacré Petit Studio in the Coeur of Montmartre
description:
In the most lively and absolutely unique district of Paris: Montmartre!

Main features :

- Recently renovated

- Fully equipped

- High speed internet : 100 Mb/s, fiber-optic cabling

- Right next to the metro (Lamarck-Caulaincourt station: 2 min walk)

- Located on the ground floor

- Shops, bars and restaurants are very close in our live neighborhood

- The bed is on a mezzanine (size: 150 x 190 cm)

- Small is beautiful :) total floor area : 14 sqm

The space

Other things to note
Electricity bill is not included in the price for long term stays.

License number
Available with a mobility lease only ("bail mobilité")
neighborhood_overview:
Half-city, half-village, and sitting above Paris, Montmartre remains the most diverse and iconic district in Paris.
Up the Butte Montmartre hill, where the studio is located, you will be treated to a spectacular view across the city with some of the best viewpoints found next to the dazzling Sacre Coeur Basilica that dominates the Montmartre skyline. At the bottom of the hill, you will discover the district of Pigalle and its attractions, such as the famous Moulin Rouge.
Montmartre is the artistic hub of Paris; while the era of Picasso, Monet and Van Gogh is over, the area still retains the bohemian vibe of the Belle Époque with an array of artists lining the streets ready to sketch your likeness for a small fee.

neighborhood_overview:
There are numerous shops and cafés nearby, and many restaurants offering a wide choice of cuisines.

description:
We follow Airbnb's cleaning and disinfection recommendations to prevent the spread of COVID-19.
Modern and quiet penthouse studio located in the cultural heart of Berlin-Neukölln, a colorfull lively multi ethnic neighborhood with many different nationalities and cultural backgrounds. Galleries, Cafés, Bars, Parks and Groceries Stores are within walking distance. Excellent public transport access only 4 blocks away. Tempelhof Airfield is reachable in just a few minutes walking.

The space
Bright and cosy Penthouse Studio with an open kitchen, private bathroom and a double size bed (140x200cm) suitable for 2 persons. An extra single size matress for a 3rd guest is available. A table with 4 chairs, a desk and a large kitchen
neighborhood_overview:
The area is full of students, artists and people from all sorts of cultural backgrounds and nationalities. It is becoming a vivid neighborhood full of bars, cafés and art galleries but still not so hipsterish like i.e. Prenzlberg. Here is Berlin like it always was, a colorfull mix of all kinds of inhabitants.
In walking distance you will find the Tempelhofer Feld, Berlin´s former airport build by the nazis and now Berlin´s biggest public park. Sporty people use the landing lanes for kite-boarding, skating and bike-riding. An urban gardening community turned part of the airport into a unique blossoming garden.
Two busy streets form the backbone of Neukölln, Karl-Marx-Str. and Hermannstr., both full of bustling cheap shops and eateries. The more cooler sites lay in the backstreets like Weserstr., Herrfurthplatz in the Shillerkietz, nearby Emser Str. or little father Kreuzberg and the so called Kreuzkölln, along many others.

The space
Piazza Campo de' Fiori è un luogo unico a Roma dove si respira ancora un'atmosfera originale e caratteristica.
Campo de Fiori infatti si contraddistingue per la sua doppia veste: al mattino la piazza è mercato popolare gremito di gente fiera e genuina che girovaga fra banchi di frutta e verdura ricordando le atmosfere perdute della Roma di una volta, la sera invece diventa invece punto d'incontro allegro e vivace per turisti e romani.

Ci si puo' perdere a guardare l'artista di strada che si improvvisa nei suoi numeri di magia oppure ci si puo' incantare ad ascoltare il sottofondo musicale del piano bar appena sotto casa o ci si puo' lasciare coccolare dal sassofonista che allieta i passan
neighborhood_overview: L'appartamento e’ collocato a Piazza Campo dei Fiori  42, nel cuore della piazza, a pochi passi da  Trastevere, proprio dietro ai Fori Imperiali, a due passi dal Pantheon e Piazza Navona. Sarà possible fare uno shopping a Via del Corso, nella splendida Rinascente, oppure correre a Villa Borgehese o rilassarsi a prendere un drink a Piazza Campo dei Fiori, zona cool dei giovani romani. Tra Campo dei Fiori, Trastevere e Piazza Navona la città e’ ricca di locali, gelaterie, piccole taverne e ristorantini, non solo turistici. Vi ricordiamo che la casa e’ talmente centrale che non avrete bisogno di utilizzare l’auto o di usare i mezzi pubblici.

Via Flavia , with a comfortable and beautiful walks through historic bu
neighborhood_overview:
The area of ​​the district Sallustian is elegant and quiet, frequented mainly by locals, but at the same time a 10-minute walk from the main station of Rome "Termini Station".
The district lies on the "COLLE QUIRINALE", the highest of the seven on which the small indigenous communities Roman parties for the conquest of the known world of the time.

It welcomes you in a heavenly atmosphere with a taste of Lisbon’s history.

The space
This 50sqm flat on a 1st floor belongs to a 18th century building.

The location is perfect. A very quiet block near to the Tejo riverside, walking distance to Cais do Sodré, Estrela, Bairro Alto and Chiado.

It can accomodate up to 3 guests. Two in a double be
neighborhood_overview:
Lapa is an ancient parish of Lisbon, dating from 1770 and situated in one of the many hills of the city with Jardim da Estrela at the top. It was in this area that the nobility and the bourgeoisie settled in the 18th century.
Today, this historical heritage is still felt.
It is one of the nicest neighborhoods of Lisbon, with large, perfectly preserved old houses, many ancient palaces and mansions. Here are concentrated most of the foreign countries embassies and also the Parliament and the official residence of the Prime Minister of Portugal (Palácio de São Bento).
Like every residential neighborhood in Lisbon, parking is paid. During Summer months parking is easier.

Totalmente renovado, a decoração de estilo ecléctico e a luz intensa no final do dia conferem ao espaço um ambiente muito confortável e acolhedor.
Perfeito para quem pretende visitar a Lisboa e relaxar, para praticar desportos náuticos, Surf (praias de Carcavelos e Guincho), jogar Golf (Estoril, Penha Longa) ou só para desfrutar das praias.

The space

O espaço foi totalmente renovado dispõem de uma kitchenette, equipada com novos eletrodomésticos (placa, frigorifio, micro-ondas, torradeira, chaleira, máquina de café dolce gusto) e loiça
neighborhood_overview:
São Pedro do Estoril está situado num dos lados do triângulo, Lisboa – Cascais – Sintra, denominado por “Linha de Cascais” ou Costa do Estoril, nome como é conhecida internacionalmente.
A Costa do Estoril fica no extremo ocidental da Europa continental, é um destino acolhedor com uma atmosfera de glamour, tranquilidade e uma natureza plena e diversificada, a 20 km da capital (Lisboa) e do aeroporto internacional de Lisboa.
O bairro de São Pedro do Estoril está situado junto à praia de São Pedro, é constituído maioritariamente por vivendas do início seculo no lado esquerdo da ribeira de Cai Agua, e no lado esquerdo, por moradias de meados do século XX. Muito arborizado e dotado de espaços de lazer, sendo de destacar o Parque das Novas Gerações (parque de skate onde são organizadas várias competições internacionais), é uma zona residencial muito carismática, segura e calma.
A praia de S.Pedro localiza-se na enseada da Bafureira, possui uma beleza muito particular pelo fato

description:

The space
Is the entire garden level floor of our home, a Georgian riverside family house, a short riverside walk from Royal Greenwich town centre and directly opposite Canary Wharf.

The flat looks out onto a pleasant garden with outside table for al fresco dining (sorry - warm weather not included!).

It has fast wifi, a small bathroom with compact bath and shower, a kitchen-in-a-cupboard (induction hob, microwave, washing machine, toaster, kettle, sink, refrigerator, freezer) and Muji sofa bed.

Guest access
Is through the garden which you are welcome to make use of. All the guests are offered : ✓ Free Wireless Internet access ✓ Fresh bed linen and towels (provided at the
neighborhood_overview:
Ballast Quay is an attractive cobbled street right beside the Thames and within easy walking distance of historic Royal Greenwich, a UNESCO World Heritage site. It is located upon the popular riverside walk from Greenwich to the Dome / O2 and is well-situated for access to local amenities including the famous Greenwich Market, shops, restaurants, cafes, pubs, theatres, cinemas, and leisure centres.

Visitor Attractions:

Greenwich's naval heritage goes back more than 600 years. We are close to Greenwich Park, London's oldest Royal Park with its panoramic views of Greenwich, Docklands and the City of London beyond.

Also close by:

neighborhood_overview:
The Mouraria is the neighborhood where the Moors were allowed to live after the conquest of Lisbon in 1147, until they were expelled along with the Jews in 1497. Little survives of that time except traces of the Moorish Fence, but curiously it is still today the most multicultural neighborhood of the city. The majority of the foreign population is from Bangladesh, with the rest being Chinese, Indian, Pakistani and Mozambican immigrants.
It is, however, a typically Lisbon neighborhood, known as the birthplace of Fado. It was here that the first great fadista lived in the nineteenth century, the mythical Severa who fell in love with an earl and took the music of the people to the aristocratic halls. Other great names linked to the Fado lived in the neighborhood, like Mariza, that grew in these streets before arriving at the great stages of the world.

Bright and tastefully furnished, this is the ideal home for guests who want to explore the city's top attractions!

The space
Welcome to my home!

Centrally located to enjoy everything the city has to offer.

This apartment can sleep up to 4 people comfortably.

Fitted with a comfy sofa, unwind in the living room after a busy day of exploring the city. The flat also has multiple windows throughout the space, allowing you to enjoy the sunlight and city views from the comfort of your home!

The kitchen is fully equipped with essential cookware and cutleries that you will need to whip up a delicious meal.

There are 2 bedrooms, one with a king-sized bed and another with a sofa bed, both with hotel-quality linens and multiple storage spaces.

The bathroom has all the amenities you will need to freshen up such as a shower, a toilet, and a sink. Fresh towels and free toiletries will also be supplie
neighborhood_overview:
The district is also connected with the Beaubourg, Ile St-Louis and the fashionable Marais, known for its hip boutiques, galleries, and eclectic bars. Once the city's Jewish quarter, a number of kosher restaurants remain. The district also houses some of the city's most important and beloved historical sites, including Notre Dame Cathedral (dominates tiny tree-lined Île de la Cité) and the elegant Place des Vosges which is a small haven of tranquility. Tourists head to Centre Pompidou, a modern art museum with an eye-catching facade.

For shopping enthusiasts, go through Rue des Francs-Bourgeois (between Paris III and IV) where you'll find various boutiques and clothing stores. There are many trendy restaurants, cafes, and bars within walking distance especially in the Marais, on the Saint-Louis Island, and in the vicinity of the Center Pompidou.

neighborhood_overview:
Mouraria is, without a doubt, one of the most traditional and multicultural neighborhoods in Lisbon. After all, it was here that the Moors came to live after D. Afonso Henriques conquered Lisbon in 1147, until they were finally expelled from Portuguese territory four centuries later.
Today, more than six centuries later, this beautiful part of the Portuguese capital continues to be the choice of more than 50 different nationalities, with the majority coming from China, India, Bangladesh, Pakistan, and Mozambique, just to name a few of the largest communities in this neighborhood.
Mouraria still is a typical Lisbon neighborhood, with its own characteristics, its own traditions and customs, and especially its unique people.

name: Central Athenian Apartment-Vintage style
description:
Η οικογένειά σας θα είναι κοντά σε ό,τι χρειαστεί σε αυτόν τον χώρο που βρίσκεται κεντρικά.

The space
Το διαμέρισμα βρίσκεται στο τρίτο όροφο σε μια ήσυχη γειτονιά των Πατησίων και είναι προσβάσιμο με ασανσέρ. Μόλις ανακαινίστηκε πλήρως με καινούργιο μπάνιο και κουζίνα, κουφώματα αλουμινίου, ηλεκτρικές τέντες και ρολά, πόρτα ασφαλείας , κλιματισμό,διατηρώντας όμως μερικές πινελιές από την ομορφιά της παλιάς Αθήνας. Όλα τα δωμάτια έχουν πρόσβαση σε μπαλκόνι. Η γειτονιά μας είναι ήσυχη, κοντά στο σχολικό συγκρότημα της Γκράβας, πολύ κοντά στην Πατησίων και στον Άγιο Λουκά. Είναι άνετο για την φιλοξενία μέχρι έξι ατόμων στις δύο κρεβατοκάμαρες και στο σαλόνι. Ο καθένας έχει το χώρο του στα ευρύχωρα δωμάτια του σπιτιού. Κατά τους χειμερινούς μήνες ενδείκνυται για την φιλοξενία εκπαιδευτικών ή φοιτητών που θα μπορούσαν να έχουν ιδιωτικό δωμάτιο με κοινή κουζίνα και μπάνιο. neighborhood_overview:
Even in Cold War times, students, cultural initiatives and intellectuals shaped the image of Prenzlauer Berg. Since the Wall came down, Prenzlauer Berg has developed into a trendy district and is known for its lively nightlife and numerous pubs, cafés and clubs.
The commercial center of the district is located at the Schönhauser Allee urban train station (five minutes from the apartment), where the "Schönhauser Allee Arcaden", a typical East German shopping center from the years immediately following reunification, attracts customers from the original Pankow district.
Prenzlauer Berg is characterized by numerous small independent shops, in each side street, especially in the Kastanienallee (ten minutes away), known locally as "Castingallee".
These days Prenzlauer Berg consists almost entirely of old buildings. There are more than 300 protected buildings. Isn't that great?!

neighborhood_overview:
Highbury is an upper class, urban neighborhood in central London that is well connected to the rest of the city by public transportation. Most of the residents here are young professionals, with quite a few younger families rounding out the population. The population is getting older, however, as these people are sticking around much longer than they used to. Many are extremely successful and make a good deal of money.

Most of the residences are apartments, which tend to be on the more expensive side. You won’t find very many single-family homes here on the market as they tend to be passed down from generation to generation.

Highbury has a healthy bar and restaurant scene. Many up-and-coming chefs live in this area so you can expect to eat extremely well. As far as shopping options, there aren’t as many stores as other neighborhoods, but there are still some great boutiques and shops here.

Highbury Fields park offers 29 acres (12 hectares) of green spa

neighborhood_overview:
Right on the edge of the historic City of London, the neighbourhood is one of the best located neighbourhoods in London. Some of London's most famous and historic sights are just a short walk away: Tower Bridge, the Tower of London, Shoreditch, Brick Lane, the Gherkin to name just a few...

During the working week, city workers and tourists make this one of the busiest areas in London. There are literally hundred of bars and restaurants in the local area. Shoreditch, Old Spitalfields Market and of course Brick Lane are just a few of the places to find some amazing food nearby.

At the weekend, the neighbourhood is a lot quieter and you'll nearly have the place to yourself. You’re within 2 minutes walk to Aldgate, 5 mins to Tower Hill Station/Tower Gateway DLR and 10 mins to Liverpool Street Station.

There are three local supermarkets within 2 minutes for you to stock up.

neighborhood_overview:
Royal Docks has seen huge development in recent years, initially industrial, the area is now becoming a hotspot for further commercial and residential development. Impressive skyscrapers make up the landscape of this area.

The nearby Thames Barrier is the world’s second-largest movable flood barrier. You can take a walking tour which focuses on the regeneration of the Royal Docks, run by Urban Glue, showing how far the area has progressed in recent history.

You also have the Thames Cable Car which runs between Greenwich peninsula and Royal Docks, also know as the Emirates Air Line it has some fantastic views of London’s skyline and also comes in handy for commuters.

Gallions Reach Shopping Park is a 10 min drive away/30 min bus, here you will find homeware and lifestyle shops, as well as restaurants.

You can reach the O2 arena in 30 mins to catch the latest concert/event and beautiful and historical Greenwich is just a short journey away.

name: Lisbon Nouveau - Apartment 3D
description:
The space
Lisbon Nouveau apartments are located in one of the city main arteries.
The nearest subway station is located right in our door front (10 meters away). The south entrance was offered by Metro de Paris and it is called the Guimard entrance, named after the famous Art Nouveau artist, Hector Guimard, best known for the design of Paris Metropolitan Stations entrances.
Inspired by the quest for modernity that moved the Art Nouveau artists, our apartments also aim to reflect the spirit of a new and trendy Lisbon, an old and traditional city with a new and vibrating life.
In the neighbourhood you can find shopping malls, food courts and numerous restaurants.
We are not far from downtown and Tagus River, and you can be there in a very short subway ride.
At walking distance you have iconic places like Praça Marquês de Pombal, Parque Eduardo VII, or the Avenida da Liberdade where you can find the most famous world brands, like Prada, Armani or Loui

neighborhood_overview:
Geygerstraße is a tiny street in the middle of Neukölln with a rich and diverse offering from the moment you leave the door.

In under 5 minutes you can walk to excellent Thai food (Mae Charoen), Italian Cafes (Caffeggiando), or Falafel/Döner (Al Hanan). Bio Company (organic grocery store) and LIDL are also within 5 minutes by foot.

You are directly connected with the U7 line and the M41 bus, which can quickly get you into Kreuxberg, Mitte, or beyond.


Stadtbad Neukölln, an early 20th century public swimming pool, is 2 minutes by foot. Enjoy a warm soak in the Kleine Halle, swim laps in the Grosse Halle, or treat yourself to the Sauna.

The space
Visit us in the heart of Alfama. Located in the middle of the main typical and central neighbourhood of Lisbon, you will breathe Portuguese culture and tradition. Alfama Chic Penabuquel is in a historical building, granting the best conditions to make you fill at home. You will live and enjoy the city as a Lisbon native and will be near to everything that matters, from nightlife to tram 28, museums and main spots. Alfama is an exciting place, full of life, colour and sunlight coming from all corners.

Guest access

neighborhood_overview: Alfama is the most typical neighbourhood that you can find in Lisbon. The narrow streets in cobble stone, the colours of the old but renovated buildings and an incredibly vibrant atmosphere surrounding you, make it an unique cocktail where you have to live to understand. This is the birthplace of Fado, Portuguese national song. Not by chance, Fado museum is just 150 meters from the apartment. Also, you can find typical restaurants where the employees or the clients take their chances in singing after a few glasses of wine. Spontaneous, friendly and joyful; this is what you will find here.

Para mim é o sítio melhor para viver em Lisboa, porque não há barulho, é seguro e não tem a poluição do centro da cidade. neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is composed of a maze of narrow streets, winding alleyways, and steep flights of steps. Its kasbah-like layout is deliberate - this is the city's ancient Arab district, and although there are no Moorish houses still standing, the tightly-packed lanes, small archways, and stone-paved terraces are full of atmosphere and great fun to explore.

Lisbon's old quarter offers many things to do. Besides the castle, there are several historic 17th-century churches in the vicinity, as well as the city's impressive cathedral. A clutch of excellent museums provide cultural diversion, and Lisbon's biggest flea market is here. Some of the best views in Lisbon are from lofty squares and viewpoints, like Portas do Sol, Senhora da Graça.

The appartmnt is surrounded by small restaurants, cafes, bars, local stores and open doors where old ladies sells liqueurs.

name: Rental unit in Lisboa · ★4.98 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
description:
Take an elevator up 7 floors, then walk up one more to arrive at a secluded terrace with a view that's worth the climb. Enjoy the terrace with a wide view of Lisbon, its rooftops, and the river.

Located a step away from the iconic Tramway 28 and "Rato" square (subway station). A step away from the masterful "Basílica da Estrela" and "Jardim da Estrela". You are at walking distance to trendy "Príncipe Real", bohemian "Bairro Alto", cosmopolitan "Chiado" and luxury "Avenida da Liberdade".

The space
Comfy attic flat with a terrace overlooking a scenic view of Lisbon rooftops & the river. The flat is located on the 8th floor and the last floor of a building from the 60s. Note: the lift goes to the 7th floor, then you have a flight of stairs to climb.

One bedroom, one bathroom, a kitchenette, and a terrace with an amazing view of Lisbon. Air conditioning for hot and cold temperatures.

The terrace is perfect for a light meal, your break
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in the "Largo do Rato" area, between the majestic "Basílica da Estrela", the peaceful "Jardim da Estrela" and the quit "Jardim das Amoreiras". Nearby there are a number of restaurants, antique shops, galleries, and bars. The subway, "Rato" station, is in front of the building and tramway 28 has a stop nearby, the perfect way to go to "Alfama". You are at walking distance to the trendy "Príncipe Real", the bohemian "Bairro Alto", the cosmopolitan "Chiado" and the luxury "Avenida da Liberdade".

name: Elegant flat in the heart of Prati-Piazza Mazzini
description:
Elegant apartment in the heart of the Prati district, 50 meters from Piazza Mazzini, about 100sqm. Flat composed of two double bedrooms, large kitchen, living room with double sofas and a bathroom. Located on the fourth floor, with elevator, the apartment has all the major comforts, also enjoys an excellent and sunny double exposure. Easily accessible by walking the Vatican and the Vatican museums.

AIR CONDITIONING IN ALL ROOMS

The space
Although it borders the Vatican, Prati is devoted to another religion: shopping. With its quiet checkered streets, this neat neighborhood effortlessly mixes business with pleasure: its elegant buildings house both important offices and classy shops; the squares and public spaces are very well kept; the distance from the center, relative, protects residents from traffic and stress, ensuring calm and exclusivity.

name: Bed and breakfast in Rome · ★4.86 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
description:
Stanza Flavia è adatto a coppie e chi viaggia per lavoro è una camera matrimoniale privata con bagno privato, un piccolo frigo ed un piccolo balcone con vista su Piazza Venezia.
E' all'interno di una Guest House all'ultimo piano di un bellissimo palazzo della fine del 1800.
Nel bagno l'acqua calda arriva senza problemi basta aprire il rubinetto e aspettare qualche secondo che diventi calda.
L'acqua del rubinetto è potabile.
Servizio pulizie giornaliere incluso nel prezzo, No cambio biancheria.

The space
La Guest House Querini era casa di mia nonna; quando è morta, i miei genitori hanno deciso di trasformarla in un Bed&Breafast ed io l’ho preso in gestione decidendo anche di viverci. Il mio appartamento è separato dagli ospiti così ognuno può avere la sua privacy, ma sono comunque nella stessa casa quindi per ogni evenienza ci sono.
La Guest House ha tre stanze ognuna con il bagno privato e un piccolo balcone.

Guest access
neighborhood_overview:
Il Quartiere è molto tranquillo ed è super collegato il che lo rende più interessante ancora. Siamo a due passi da Monti, quartiere storico romano e molto frequentato; la famosa Piazzetta di Monti è il luogo perfetto per bersi un bicchiere di vino o una birra fresca seduto sulle scalette della fontana, il clima romano permette questo quasi tutto l'anno. Monti inoltre è un mix tra la storia di Roma (Fori imperiali,Colosseo...) e la Roma mondana e moderna.
Vittoriano, Palazzo delle Esposizioni, Campidoglio, Piazza Venezia, Via del Corso, Pantheon, Fontana di Trevi e Piazza di Spagna sono raggiungibili a piedi o in metro in 10-20 minuti.
Metro Repubblica è la stessa linea che porta al Vaticano e a Termini ci sono entrambe le linee della metro. Inoltre in Piazza della Repubblica,che è a 2 minuti a piedi da noi, potrete visitare la bellissima Basilica di Santa Maria degli Angeli e le Terme di Diocleziano.

name: Family home in beautiful desirable neighbourhood
description:
Welcome to our family home. We are letting it out while we are on holiday.
This is a Span house (designed by architect Eric Lions) located in sought after Blackheath (20 minutes walk from Greenwich Park, 8 minutes walk from the train station, then 15 minutes on a train to London Bridge).
This is an ideal house for a family holiday. We have children's books, toys, everything you might need for a baby, back garden, and a lovely green area on our street with swings and lots of space to run around.

The space
You will have access to two bedrooms, an open large living space and semi-open plan kitchen. There is also a back garden and a green open communal area on our street.

Other things to note
This is our home, so our personal items will be there. The third bedroom in the house is not included in the listing and will be used to store some of our personal items.
neighborhood_overview: Our house is located on the Cator Estate, a beautiful private state which attracts designer and architect residents and architectural walking tours. Blackheath is a great location for families for its easy city commute and village feel. Alongside Georgian homes, trendy wine bars, fantastic bakeries, and pavement cafes, including a branch of upscale The Ivy, look out over the open green space of Blackheath Common. Blackheath Farmer's Market draws locals for Sunday shopping, while classical music lovers get their fill at Blackheath Halls.

name: Light and airy apartment in Belsize Park
description:
The ideal space for a family or group of friends looking to explore London.

This apartment has been recently refurbished, with an airy feel and designer furniture. Excellently located, and including access to a lovely outside terrace space!

The space
A three bedroom apartment, with two king sized beds and one double.

The apartment also has a beautiful, well-stocked kitchen, and a lovely light and airy living room.

This is one of the few apartments in this part of London that also has access to an outside space for you to enjoy.

A ten-minute walk from Northern, Jubilee and Metropolitain Line stations, the house is perfectly located for getting into the centre, but set in a quiet residential area near the park.
neighborhood_overview: The house is a 10-minute walk from Hampstead Heath, one of London's loveliest parks. neighborhood_overview: The house is on the popular Progress estate, conservation area. Eltham palace is a beautiful historical place to visit as are the Pleasance Park and Tudor barn.

name: Condo in Cascais · ★4.88 · 2 bedrooms · 4 beds · 1 bath
description:
Lys og flott leilighet i vakre omgivelser. Gåavstand til sentrum, strender, togstasjon og masse spisesteder til glede for voksne og barn. Stort og fint ferskvaremarked like i nærheten, følg stien i parken som er foran huset og du er fremme på 12 minutter. Leiligheten er 30 minutter kjøretur fra flyplassen. Matbutikk 100 meter fra huset, samt kafe og restauranter. Leiligheten har alt du trenger for et trivelig opphold. Bad med vaskemaskin og tørketrommel.

The space
Leiligheten ligger fint til. Fin utsikt til Sintra mot nord, og hav mot sør. Du ser soloppgang fra soverommet, og på dagen er solen rett over huset slik at leiligheten holder seg kjølig i løpet av dagen. Like nedenfor huset er det gårdsbruk og et flott turområde som vi går igjennom på vei til byen. Se på bilder for mer informasjon.

Other things to note
Leiligheten har to små soverom. Ett av rommene er uten vindu, og har et eget integrert system for inn og utlufting.
neighborhood_overview:
Flott nabolag, rett ved et historisk turområde "Ribeira das vinhas" med sauer og høner som gir en følelse av å bo på landet, den følelsen kan også høres. Hvis du plages av dyrelyder anbefaler jeg øreplugg i ett øre når du sover på hovedsoverommet, det er ikke mye lyd, men med plugg er det null lyd. Vi bruker denne parken til å gå tur i, og vi bruker også veien igjennom parken for å gå til ferskvaremsrkeder (12 minutter å gå), og til stranden (15 minutter å gå).

Leiligheten har god utsikt over Sintra og havet.

neighborhood_overview: Mets is a small neighborhood, a heartbeat from all the main touristic attractions of the city center(it is a 10 minutes walk from Acropolis and just 5 minutes from Kallimarmaro Stadium)but it is not touristic at all. It is located on Ardittos hill. A little bit of Montmartre, a little bit of East London, this is a place you should discover if you want to visit one of the most charming areas of Athens. Mets took its name from the beer house that was established on the hill in 1870 by the Bavarians who accompanied King Otto to Greece. In the 19th century, due to the area's proximity to the Palace and the city center, the neighborhood was populated by middle-class families who built elegant, big neoclassical houses and changed the character of the area completely. It is now considered one of the most stylish neighborhoods of the city. Many artists, musicians, actors, painters have moved in Mets and have given it a more bohemian character. neighborhood_overview:
The studio is directly located at the Hasenheide park with its green meadows, an open-air cinema and the open-air swimming pool Neukölln.

An organic supermarket is directly at the corner and one of the best gym’s of Berlin “Holmes Place” is in 5 minutes walking distance.

In the street where the studio is located you will find delicious restaurants like the "Cocolo Ramen" and within 5 minutes walking distance you will reach the famous Maybach and Paul-Linke boulevard with plenty of restaurants and a biweekly farmers market. Not to mention all the bars and clubs that you will be able to experience in Kreuzberg.

The studio is easy to access with public transport and all the mayor car, motor bike and bike sharing apps e.g. Car2Go, DriveNow, Miles, WeShare and Tier are working here.

If you love Berlin, there is no better place than this to experience it.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished flat is located in Old Street, a lively district in northeast Central London. This historic neighborhood was the setting for Britain's first permanent playhouse, which was located on Curtain Road. William Shakespeare's theater company first performed Henry IV and Romeo and Juliet right in the heart of present day Old Street. Another neighborhood landmark is St. Luke's Church, which opened in the early 18th century and presently enjoys a new life as a music centre that hosts rehearsals and community events. Old Street has a flourishing restaurant scene, and there are plenty of pubs where you can unwind after work. The Northern line serves the neighborhood, and it's also easy to get around Old Street by bus.

Mouraria is a very authentically Lisbon neighborhood, known as the birthplace of Fado.

This changing "Bairro" is turning into one of Lisbon's more fashionable neighborhoods.

neighborhood_overview:
The Mouraria (moorish quarter) is a Lisbon neighborhood located between Martim Moniz and the Castle of S. Jorge. In it stayed the Moors who remained after the conquest of the city, but today the neighborhood is best known as the birthplace of Fado.

You can climb the hill for spectacular views of the nearby Acropolis, the whole city, and the Aegean Sea. You can stroll the pedestrian streets and explore the historic sites on the other side of Philopappos Hill. There are plenty of restaurants and tavernas nearby. Philopappou Hill can also be reached with the Athens Metro, exiting at Thissio or Acropolis stations.

neighborhood_overview:
We are in the heart of Rome, near the famous Campo de Fiori, a lively market place in the morning that at night turns into the center of nightlife, all in a beautiful setting full of history.
For centuries, Campo de 'Fiori was the main stage for public executions. Here in 1600, was buried Giordano Bruno, whose statue dominates the center of the square.
Do not miss nearby, the historic streets with traditional shops that still carry the name of the artisans who once worked there, such as Via dei Baullari, Via dei Cappellari or via dei Giubbonari. If you are looking for antiques take a stroll through the shops of Via Margutta, Via Giulia, Via dei Banchi Vecchi and via dei Coronari, while in Via del Pellegrino and Via del Governo Vecchio you can find vintage shops.From this strategic area, you can easily walk to many extraordinary places such as Castel Sant'Angelo, Piazza di Spagna, Trevi Fountain, St. Peter's Basilica, the Colosseum and the Roman Forum.

Less than 10 minute walk to New Cross Gate station: from there it's one stop to London Bridge and the South Bank; 20 minutes to Shoreditch and the City of London; and 25 minutes to Oxford Circus.

Up and coming Peckham Rye is half hour walk with Greenwich Park within half an hour on the bus.

The space
You will be staying on the lower ground floor of a Victorian town-house on the edge of Zone 1 / 2 of London.

The basement flat is recently refurbished and has a new everything - kitchen and bathroom included. We have endeavoured to keep things simple but ensure we provide you with everything you need for a comfortable stay.

We moved here because it is a fantastic area for families, because there is a strong community atmosphere
neighborhood_overview:
The stuff we like about Telegraph Hill and the surrounding area...

The Hill Station Community Cafe - great breakfasts and brunches, pretty much the centre of the local community.

Telegraph Hill Park - there are two parts, one for the kids and the other for dogs walkers (the latter has views of the whole of London).

Local pubs... Skeehans - a little rough round the edges but great atmosphere and, if you pick the right night, you might get invited to a lock-in. The White Hart pub - great selection of beers at the bottom of the hill and a late license. The Telegraph at the Earl of Danby - great roasts and a lovely fire.

Goldsmiths - the famous art college.

Head west on the bus and you come to the up and coming Peckham Rye, with lots of bars and restaurants. A bit further on you come to Camberwell, Herne Hill and Brixton - more great places to eat and drink and with the amazing Brockwell Park close by.

In Berlin bieten sich zahlreiche Möglichkeiten, historische und moderne Kultur besuchen, sich zu erholen, das Zusammenwachsen von Ost und West intensiv und lebendig erleben. Besondere Anziehungspunkten sind der historische Stadtkern mit dem Brandenburger Tor und der Straße unter den Linden sowie dem angrenzenden Regierungsviertel, einzigartige Museen, eine traditionsreiche Industriekultur, moderne Architektur oder die städtischen Naherholungsgebiete.
Auf Wunsch gestalten wir Stadtführungen mit sachkundigen Stadtführern. Hierzu beraten wir Sie gern. Für Gruppen bis 8 Personen bieten wir Führungen für 20 Euro an, jede weitere Person 2 Euro. Die Nutzung des Berliner Nahverkehrs kostet extra.

neighborhood_overview: The Silicon Docks are a fast changing yet very historic area of Dublin.  Centrally located with many wonderful pubs, restaurants and independent stores, the area has in recent years become a vibrant mix of long time resident friendly Dubliners and a diverse group of international residents working primarily in international technology or finance multinationals.  The area’s transformation is typified by the skyline of the Bolands Quay development, which visible from the floor -to-ceiling windows in the living room.   It was a large working mill for many decades and after a multi year redevelopment has now been relaunched as Google’s EMEA headquarters.

neighborhood_overview:
I've lived here for many years - it's a close local community and I can't imagine a better location. Situated between Old St, Clerkenwell, Hoxton and Shoreditch you've got all you need right around you in the most vibrant part of London. And it's a great base to explore from, too. Starting outside, there's a good supermarket and a daily street food market just 50yds away. The Barbican Arts Centre is just two minutes' walk (cinema, theatre, concert hall, art gallery, library, cafes, restaurants), and lots of other cafés, shops etc. are all around. Brick lane, Spitalfields and Columbia Rd markets are all within walking distance.

For summer relaxing there's a little community park with a tiny but great mobile cafe (fantastic flat whites and banana muffins), and there are the waterside fountains at the Barbican centre where you can sunbathe with the ducks. neighborhood_overview:
Few places bustle like Battersea these days, with top-notch restaurants, bars and boozers bringing 'em in from far and wide. The Battersea Arts Centre continues to showcase some of the best in the business, and the zoo and the park are great for kids (and kids within). The Pump House Gallery is as good as ever and then there's the heliport, with choppers taking you for some seriously impressive views across our fair city.
Battersea has plenty of shops and restaurants — close to Clapham Junction, up St John’s Road, continuing along Northcote Road and up the hill from the junction along Lavender Hill and Battersea Rise.
Northcote Road is dominated by mid-market chains such as Jigsaw, Whistles and Phase Eight and youth brands White Stuff and Jack Wills. Two long-standing butchers, Dove & Son and Hennessy, along with sports shop Capstick and jewellers Asquiths have survived other local independents.
Celebrity chef Gordon Ramsay’s London House restaurant in Battersea Square

neighborhood_overview:
O Sabugo é uma aldeia com cerca de 1500 habitantes, rica em história, tradições e cultura popular. Era um ponto de passagem dos nossos Reis quando iam para Mafra que aqui paravam para se refrescarem e darem de beber aos animais no chafariz construído no reinado de D. João V, no ano de 1782.
Sintra é Património da Humanidade (Unesco), com muitos lugares para visitar, incluindo: Museu de Arte Moderna, Castelo dos Mouro, Palácio da Vila; Palácio da Pena, Quinta da Regaleira, etc. Espectáculos musicais e outros eventos culturais encontram-se na Casa da Pinheira num ficheiro para consulta.

The apartment is within walking distance of the square of graça where the flea market is held every Tuesday and Saturday. Apart from traditional trinkets, you can also buy second-hand clothes, books, records, and if you search well, you can find some valuable antiques. The apartment is at an easy walk (about 20min) to the city center. If you prefer you can go on the tram 28 (about 10min) whose route passes the most important and beautiful sights of Lisbon. A "must" not to be missed! You are at a walking distance from everything: the Castle (S. Jorge), Baixa, Chiado and Bairro Alto. Nearby you can also go to viewpoints with fantastic views of the castle of Sao Jorge, the Tagus river and on the roofs of houses. very nice park with sheep in it, a short walk from the flat, called Landschaftspark Herzberge.

Shopping for food stuffs you can goto one of the grocery stores, all within 8 minutes of walking. If household items are needed there is a mall at the U­ Bahn stop Frankfurter Allee, 2 stops with the U­ Bahn from S/U Bahn Lichtenberg direction Alexander Platz.

A good bakery can be found on the Rudiger Str. corner Siegfried Str. If you haven’t eaten your fill of German bread then you’re missing out.

name: Whole top floor, two bedrooms, private bathroom.
description:
Our lovely, quiet home is set in leafy Muswell Hill, only 20 minutes by tube from Central London. The top (second) floor looks mainly south over beautiful gardens towards elegant Victorian houses. The tube and the two vibrant London 'villages' of Muswell Hill and Crouch End (cafes, cinemas etc.) are close by. Woods, open spaces and Alexandra Palace are even nearer. We offer a healthy vegan breakfast and a warm, informed welcome to London. Our two quiet, affectionate greyhounds are also vegan!

The space
The top-floor is self-contained and is all yours, whether you require one or both bedrooms. Tea/coffee facilities are provided, also wi-fi and a work-top. The private bathroom has a shower and a slipper roll-top bath - ideal for reading in! Being at the back of the house, away from the road, the space is very quiet and, in season, catches the sun all day, including beautiful sunrises ...if you are up that early!
We try to be as plastic free as possible so of
neighborhood_overview: Muswell Hill, green and relaxed, yet so close and so well connected to Central London, is a well-kept tourist secret of great interest. Parking is free in and around our street. Alexandra Palace and Park are here and close by and there are numerous lovely walks - eg Highgate Woods, Queens Woods and smaller parks also with cafes. Muswell Hill and Crouch End have an array of diverse cafes, pubs, restaurants and cinemas. HIghgate Village is nearby, charming with quaint streets, pubs and cafes. Highgate Cemetery is fascinating to visit for the graves of Karl Marx, Charles Dickens and many other notables.  Kenwood House, Hampstead Heath and Hampstead Village are a short drive away, with plenty of parking facilities. Camden Market is 10 minutes away by tube and 20 by bus. From Camden Town, you can walk through beautiful Regents Park to the centre of London.

neighborhood_overview: Poblenou is Catalan for 'New Village', and is situated with the Mediterranean Sea on one side and the beautiful Parc de la Ciutadella on the other. Historically, the area was one of the main industrial zones of the city, however today, Poblenou is surrounded by many new developments, including the neighbourhoods of Vila Olímpica, where the athletes competing in the 1992 Olympics resided, and Diagonal Mar. The increase in new facilities alongside the town's proximity to the Barcelona beaches and excellent public transportation services, has brought many artists and young professionals to the Poblenou. Rambla de Poblenou is the main avenue in the neighbourhood and it is said to be a more authentic alternative to the Ramblas you will find in the city centre. It has a great ambience and is home to many fantastic bars, cafés and restaurants. The great esplanade of El Fòrum is located right near Poblenou, though technically in the Diagonal Mar area. Fly into Fiumicino Int’l airport, and you'll be home within an hour. Once you step outside of your apartment, the bus station is at 2-minute walk and the Repubblica metro stop is just a 5-minute walk away, getting you all around Rome. However, the best way to visit Rome is on foot. Fancied a cultural stroll, why not walk 20 minutes to the famous Coliseum and the Roman Forum, or if you want something closer walk to the Trevi Fountain, approximately 15-minute walk, and to the Spanish Steps.

On the southern tip of the Arroios parish, Pena is a family neighbourhood, home to the Italian Embassy, German Embassy, grassy parks and ponds… and the birthplace of Amália Rodrigues.

“This experience is for those wanting to chat up old neighbours and dive into Lisbon’s rhythm.“

Our neighborhood funicular (trolley), 120-year old Elevador do Lavra, is one of the most charming amenities. The first funicular in Lisbon, Elevador do Lavra rattles up and down the hillside every 15 minutes, every day. Soon you’ll be riding like a local, cheerfully showing the tourists how and where to punch their tickets.

Stay in a quiet, comfortable home with 2 double bedrooms in a Georgian terrace in the heart of historic Maritime Greenwich. The house is just minutes from the beautiful and expansive Greenwich Park, Blackheath common and the Thames riverside for local walks and exercise. For work in the City or Canary Wharf districts, it is an easy 20 minute transport ride on regular local transport links.

The space
This is my home when I'm not away travelling, and you would be warmly welcomed to it.
The house has an open ground floor lounge and dining room leading out through a glazed modern kitchen and breakfast room to a quiet private garden - in a safe, quiet neighbourhood. Decorated throughout in a comfortable, relaxed style which mixes traditional features with modern amenities.
The 1st floor bedrooms have king size beds, built-in wardrobes, and fresh warm linens and towels. The large traditional bathroom is immediately next door and features an imposing and indul
neighborhood_overview:
The house is set in a quiet terrace of Georgian houses minutes from Greenwich Park, the Royal Observatory, and the Royal Naval College - now the University of Greenwich.
If you like exercise, stride up the hill to Blackheath common, and run back through the park - catching the deer and squirrels on the way. If you're a little more sedate, mooch the markets, trawl the great local pubs, sample international cuisine or simply watch the river go by... Looking for history and culture? Feast on the Maritime Museum, Royal Observatory and Naval College or indulge yourself in the multiple festivals Greenwich offers, from Comedy through International Theatre & Tall Ships. Big venues? The 02 and Excel are a 10 and 20 minute journey away.

description:
Located in the heart of Dublin city, this beautiful two bedroom house is situated only 100m from the entrance to the Guinness Storehouse. The house was originally built by Guinness for their employees and has been recently renovated. It boasts two bedrooms with double beds, a beautiful new bathroom, a sitting room with a fireplace, two sofa beds and a Harry Potter bed under the stairs. It can sleep up to seven people comfortably and overlooks a beautiful old church with a park in the back.

The space
There is a big cooker in the kitchen that is perfect for large groups or families who wish to try and recreate Irish cooking at home. There is a small back garden that overlooks St Catherine's, a medieval church. The bedrooms have plenty of storage space and there are electric blankets on the double beds in each room. There is a large 55" TV in the sitting room that has Netflix and Amazon Prime. There is WiFi in the house and a roaring fireplace with plenty of turf,
neighborhood_overview: Located just off Thomas St and only 100m from the Guinness Storehouse, this house is ideally located in a residential area and around the corner from the Liberty Markets. The Teeling Whiskey factory is only a five minute walk from the house and the Jameson factory is just across the river in the other direction. The Brazen Head, the oldest pub in Ireland, is a five minute walk towards the river. Heuston Station, the central train station, is eight minutes away and Phoenix Park, the largest public park in Europe, is just beyond it. The Dublin Zoo, the oldest zoo in Europe, is located inside Phoenix Park.

It is very popular with Parisians, who often meet around the square for the departure of major eventsThis square is the origin of its name. General Denfert-Rochereau was a military man at the end of the 19th century who distinguished himself during the 1870 war between France and the Prussians. This is also the reason why the Lion of Belfort occupies masterfully the center of the square. This statue was created by the sculptor Bartholdi (who was also the creator of the Statue of Liberty) and was bought by the city of Paris in 1879. This gigantic lion of 4 meters high and 7 meters wide was initially intended to be installed in the Buttes Chaumont (in the 19th district of Paris). Crowds flock to this edgy epicenter to experience its sultry past and trendy present. WEST END

Theatres, shops, pubs, clubs, landmarks, and lounges—no matter how many times you visit, you'll never see the same neighbourhood twice. neighborhood_overview:
In Roman dialect, Trastevere means "across the Tiber”. This picturesque medieval area in fact is located on the west bank of the Tiber.
Part of the historical centre of Rome, Trastevere is the perfect place to glimpse a bit of the old world while still enjoying the lifestyle of today's Romans. From the cobblestone streets to the overhanging laundry lines, senses are pleasantly awakened with every step you take in this bohemian neighborhood.
Equidistant from the Coliseum and the Vatican, Trastevere is an ideal place to discover the secrets of Rome on foot. Saint Peter and the Vatican city are about twenty minutes away and upon crossing the Tiber you get to Campo dei Fiori, Piazza Navona, the Spanish Steps, the Roman Forum, and many other sights, in no time at all (15 to 30 minutes walks).

name: Cozy and elegant apartment in the heart of Paris
description:
Welcome to our apartment in the heart of the historical Parisian neighborhood Le Marais.
Our cozy mansard-flat is in an historical building that dates back to the XVIII Century, with an elegant courtyard.
It is few floors up from one of the most typical Parisian streets, full of boutiques, gardens and jazz players - yet, it is so peaceful you will relax straightaway. A nice view on the roofs, featuring Notre Dame and Panthéon on the skyline, or a warm bath might help, too.

The space
The apartment has two rooms.
You will have your own room, with dressing and heating.
The flat is kind of all, but features everything needed.
neighborhood_overview:
Le Marais is a fairytale from the Middle Age Century, and stayed almost the same from that. There's nothing much to say about that: you might have already heard about its streets, its shops, its classy restaurants and typical bistrot, its unique atmosphere.
It's so lively you will find many different shops and moods - la Perle Café, right under our house, is intellectual and social. Clothing boutiques range from Supreme, a few meters away, a street clothing company, and Sandro, the most typical Parisian girl brand.
The apartment is super central, which means that it is a few steps away from some of the highlights of the city (Cathedral, Hotel de Ville, BHV Marais...) and I will be more than happy to give you any tip on not-to-miss hidden attractions.

name: Rental unit in Rome · ★4.95 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
description:
For those of you who are not interested in loads of space, we offer a small (14 sqm) but cosy and well equipped studio for your stay in Rome. We have renovated a former wash house and transformed it into a modern and refined pied à terre with a hydro massage shower and usb wall ports, your comfort being our main concern. Our studio is located in Villa Certosa, a friendly neighborhood (almost a small town) in Rome, 15 mins by tram from Termini Station and 10 mins on foot from the popular Pigneto.

The space
The former wash house (years ago the residents used to wash their own laundry by hand) is now a small and extremely well furnished studio ideal for single travelers who appreciate and respect a space that has been studied and decorated with love.

There is a comfortable bed (with many pillows), a desk (with the Lonely Planet guidebook in English), and a well equipped kitchenette (with induction hob, sink, mini fridge, and small electric oven). The bath
neighborhood_overview: Located in the midst of the Mandrione (with its Roman aqueduct), the Pigneto (with its intense nightlife), and Torpignattara (with its multi-ethnicity), Villa Certosa is an authentic "small town" within the city of Rome. Villa Certosa is a close community that extends along its lovely main street, Via dei Savorgnan. Here you find small houses built during the First World War, two restaurants (one specializes in seafood anf the other in traditional Roman food), two wineries, one bakery, and five minutes away, a supermarket (24/7). You will enjoy being away from the confusion of the tourist crowds and you will be able to savor a genuine Roman atmosphere, which has been, and still is, the location for many movies and tv series set in the "real" Rome. The Pigneto area, with its many restaurants, pizzerias and pubs, where you can enjoy an aperitivo or a drink after dinner, can be reached on foot in 10 minutes.

Known for its antique shops, gardens, viewpoints and a growing gay population, Príncipe Real is emerging as an interesting shopping destination due to a growing number of designer shops. It remains primarily a residential neighbourhood known for its palaces and two of the most peaceful squares in the city, Príncipe Real and Flores.

Tungsten lights hanging over low-levelled wiring is probably the first thing you notice in the area. Its tourism footfall centers around the Kallimarmaro in all-white marble, the National Gallery.
Nevertheless, the curious its the unpretentious feel and its homey charm abundant in all the cafés and places around. The sunlight during the morning hours hits the walls of Pagrati and creates that buzzing feel, adding so much to it. Greek delis, art shops and indie galleries share streets with pizzerias, casual tavernas and gourmet restaurants. neighborhood_overview: This Brand New apartment lies off one of the main avenues leading to the historic centre of Athens. The National Archaeological Museum is just a nine minute walk and well worth a visit, while the new Hellenic Motor Museum is just two blocks away, on Ioulianou Street. neighborhood_overview:
PÈRE LACHAISE CEMETERY
The Père-Lachaise Cemetery is probably the most famous cemetery in Paris, if not in the world. And we understand why by visiting it. Although Paris is full of attractive cemeteries (Montparnasse, Montmartre, Batignolles), this one is the most surprising, and the most beautiful, by many aspects.
First of all, of course, because it welcomes a tremendous amount of celebrities from all over the world. But also because during your walk in its paved streets, you will discover a great number of plant species, something that one does not necessarily expect to find here. Cherry trees, maples, chestnut trees, weeping willows, walnut trees... The Père-Lachaise cemetery has about 5000 trees representing about 50 different species spread over an area of 44 hectares. This makes the place the largest green space in Paris!

My home is desirably located in the heart of East London; London Fields, Shoreditch, Brick Lane, Dalston, Hackney Downs and Haggerston are within walking distance. Some of London's best cafes, bars and co-working spaces are in the buildings next to mine and spread within a few blocks.
