neighborhood_overview:
The Piramide Testaccio district is located in the southeastern part of Rome, near the historic center. The area is very lively and multicultural, with many businesses, restaurants, bars and nightclubs.

The area takes its name from the Cestia Pyramid, an ancient Roman tomb that is located right in the center of the neighborhood. It is a pyramidal monument, about 36 meters high, built around 12 B.C.

Testaccio is one of the most characteristic areas of the neighborhood. It is a historic area that in the past hosted the fish market of Rome. Today it is a very popular area by both Romans and tourists, thanks to its numerous restaurants, restaurants and the Testaccio market that offer typical specialties of Roman cuisine. In addition, in this area there is also Eataly Roma, the largest food and wine center in the world where you can buy, eat and study high-quality food and drinks.

description:
Located in Alfama, a very traditional neighborhood, this fully renewed one bedroom apartment with queen size bed and sheets of the highest quality, also has a comfortable living room with lots of light and a kitchen equipped with everything you need to feel at home!
Surrounded by restaurants, wine bars and fado houses, this is the perfect choice for those who want to enjoy the rich local cultural without giving up comfort.

The space
In the apartment you will find:

- Dining / living room with sofa bed and dining table for 4 people.

- Bedroom with queen bed

- Bathroom with bath and shower

- Extraordinary cotton sheets, towels and everything.

neighborhood_overview:
Alfama is one of the neighborhoods that survived the devastating earthquake of 1755. The neighborhood keeps its image of clothes stretched out on windows, its narrow stairs, flowers and alleys ...
Alfama is increasingly a center of culture. A place of hidden corners and narrow streets, where you'll love to walk.
Music is an inexorable feature of the neighborhood. It is common to walk through the streets of Alfama and listen to the Fado leaving through the local doors and windows; from time to time it comes accompanied by the typical smell of roasted sardines.
Alfama is also well-known among the locals for countless artists of Portuguese popular music, with their melancholy melodies, lyrics on the sea, homesickness, ordinary life and other themes common to the style.

name: Riverside city apartment, private double room
description:
Want to experience Dublin like a local? Welcome to our home! Situated in a 4-story building with views of the Liffey River, our modern city apartment is a fantastic place to stay close to many of Dublin's attractions and a quick hop to the city's vibrant heart.

The space
Our cozy riverside apartment is a quiet and peaceful oasis from the hustle and bustle of the city. It has beautiful hardwood floors and big windows which give us lots of natural light even during the winter when the Dublin skies are gray. You will be sharing the space with my husband and I, we are a well-travelled, multicultural couple in our late 30s who work full-time. You will have your own private double bedroom fully furnished with a comfy super king-sized bed, bedside table, large mirror and wardrobe space for your belongings. The bathroom is shared with us but it has everything you'd need to feel like home and we provide fresh towels, body wash, shampoo and hair-dryer.

Guest
neighborhood_overview: We are lucky to live in one of the greenest areas of Dublin city. The gorgeous Phoenix Park, one of the largest enclosed urban parks in Europe, is our favorite oasis as you can walk or ride a bicycle for miles and it's just a few minutes walk away. The Irish National War Memorial Gardens is also right next to our apartment. You can go for a stroll down by the bank of the Liffey and watch the local rowing teams practice throughout the spring and summer. Up the road lies Kilmainham, home to the Kilmainham Gaol and the Royal Hospital.  The former is now a museum and the later houses the Irish Museum of Modern Art. Both are well worth visiting. The people in our building and neighborhood are quiet and friendly. The area is safe and clean.

name: 🥐 Superb apartment - Montmatre - 2 pers 🥐
description:
Come and discover my apartment (40 m2) located in the heart of the 18th arrondissement in the famous Montmartre district!

This apartment can accommodate up to 2 people, it is located on the 4th floor (no elevator) and is very well equipped.

It is surrounded by shops for shopping, bakeries, grocery stores, restaurants and bars and plenty of transport to visit the tourist sites of Paris. Do not hesitate !

The space
You will enjoy a quiet and very bright accommodation. You will surely appreciate the moldings on the ceiling, the old parquet floor, the decorative fireplace and the modernity of the equipment. The apartment is composed:

🌟 an equipped kitchen (Freezer, Oven, Espresso coffee machine, Refrigerator, hob, Kettle and everything you need to cook as if you were at home ...),

Lumineux a bright living room with a relaxation area,

🌟 a dining area for lunch / dinner,

🌟 a bedroom with a double bed,
neighborhood_overview:
The 18th century is fortunate to have one of the most beautiful mounds in Paris: the Butte Montmartre. If the bravest dare to brave it on foot, we lend ourselves to the charm of yesteryear by taking the funicular. On the descent, we will walk around the Abbesses, a small village par excellence, where life is good.
The Sacré-Coeur is the second most visited religious monument. If the church itself is sublime, we also savor the view of all of Paris from its forecourt: the Eiffel Tower, typically Parisian roofs. We love to stroll on the sloping lawn.

The Abbesses district and more particularly the rue des Martyrs has its strong faces. Michou and his famous blue glasses are among them. His cabaret at number 80 rue has been a must since 1956!

The Moulin Rouge and its rich history illuminate Pigalle. Edith Piaf, Mistinguette, Frank Sinatra ... The cabaret was the theater of very great moments. Today, we’re going there to enjoy a colorful show. To do at least once!

In the morning, you could even glimpse the butcher and the barmen from across the street compete in how to best feed the seagull. And let's not forget the music. In the morning we have church bells, and the accordionists during lunch and dinner. Despite the 'touristy' location, this neighbourhood has truly retained all its little roman charm, a kind of small village in the big eternal city.

The space

Set in the 16th district, this trendy refurbished flat uses a minimalist element in its design and decor. The calming and clutter-free ambiance will encourage guests to unwind after a long day in the metropolis.

neighborhood_overview:
The swanky 16th Arr. boasts elegant residential neighborhoods with stately old houses and beautiful art-deco buildings, fine restaurants, world-class museums (both big and small), famous stadiums and leafy parks. It is also home to foreign embassies and renowned museums, including the Fondation Louis Vuitton and the Palais de Tokyo with its contemporary art.

From larger institutions such as the Modern Art Museum of the City of Paris to smaller ones like the Marmottan-Monet Museum and Musee Baccarat, there's plenty in store here for arts and culture aficionados.

Looking for family-friendly activities? Head to the Bois de Boulogne for its boating lakes and kids' theme park.

If you want to see how well-off Parisians live, it's worth a Metro ride to Passy. You'll be rewarded with an enclave of narrow streets with some of the best luxury food shopping in Paris as well as the Maison de Balzac, a house museum where the novelist once lived.

Enjoy!

description:
Welcome to our White & Blue Vintage Home and prepare yourself for a wonderful stay in Lisbon. This beautiful flat was fully renovated in November 2020, and maintains many so-typical charming features of older Lisbon, including our white & blue tile. What are you waiting for, take a peek for yourself!

The space
You will notice all the care and detail put in the refurbishment of this charming flat, which still maintains many of the original features of historical flats like this one: from the white & blue tiles, to the stoned structure that holds the kitchen chimney, not forgetting the beautiful original flooring, all complemented with some touches of vintage decor mixed with modern appliances and materials.

You'll be finding the following in our vintage flat:
- 2 double bedrooms
- 1 small interior bedroom / office space
- 2 walk-in shower bathrooms with toilet (one with a bidet as well)
- 1 spacious living & dining area / open space
neighborhood_overview:
Imagine a hill showcasing fantastic views over Lisbon... Well that's pretty much our favourite neighborhood in Lisbon - Graça!!! And our NEST is located just a few minutes walking from the very heart of Graça, and just by a dozen of small bakeries, supermarkets, coffee shops and local restaurants...

This hill showcases the most amazing landscape of the city, so you really cannot miss going for a coffee at the cafeteria next to Graça's church, or going to "Miradouro Senhora do Monte" (both less than 10 minutes walking from the Nest) and getting blown away by the views. Really close to the flat you'll have the historical 28 electrical tram line (you must jump in and take a right all the way down to downtown Baixa - or upwards if you're coming back home), but if you just prefer to take a walk (which we fully recommend) you'll find awesome places nearby, like the Alfama neighborhood and the Panteão Nacional (10 min), St. Jorge Castle (15 min away), Baixa downtown is about 25 min

name: Rental unit in Lisboa · ★4.77 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
description:
This charming and renovated apartment is located in the heart of Alfama and offers a wonderful view over the old rooftops of Alfama, the most typical and historic neighbourhood of Lisbon.
You’ll find everything you need to make the best out of your journey in Lisbon!

The space
This flat provides everything you need for an unforgettable experience.
It’s a 2nd floor of a typical Lisbon building, without elevator. Able to accommodate up to 4 guests.
It has one bedroom (double bed), a living room (with double sofa bed - when open it has 140x200 cm) a kitchen and a bathroom. Besides the double bed and sofa, you will also have access to a mezzanine, with two single matresses. Its use is responsability of the guests since the access hasn't fixed stairs, it's an atipical extra accomodation.
Bedding and towels are provided. There is also a hair dryer, free internet access through Wi-Fi and the kitchen is fully equipped .

Guest access<
neighborhood_overview:
This apartment is located in the historical neighborhood of Alfama, just below the Church of Santo Estêvão. One or two minutes walking from the Fado Museum.

Alfama, as most of Lisbon’s historical centre, is hilly and there are staircases all over the distric. And many restricted areas to cars so there is no direct access to cars to the building entrance.

From here you can easily reach most of Lisbon attractions and discover the delicious and unique flavours of Lisbon: Viewpoints of Portas do Sol, Graça and Senhora do Monte; St Georges Castle, Fado Museum, craft shops, cafes, restaurants, fado-houses, the flea market and easy access to other typical neighbourhoods as Bairro Alto, Chiado and Baixa. It is also within a walking distance the Santa Apolónia train and metro Station, the famous E28 tram and direct public transportation to Belém or Parque das Nações.

name: Boutique hotel in Paris · ★4.33 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
description:
The Hotel Petit Paris is located on Rue Saint-Jacques between the Panthéon and Luxembourg Gardens, right in the heart of the Latin Quarter.

A short walk from Saint-Germain-des-Prés, this boutique hotel takes you on a luxurious trip through time as it invites you to discover the history of Paris.

The space
This hotel is located between the Panthéon and the Luxembourg Garden, in the heart of the Quartier Latin.
It offers a luxurious journey back in time, an invitation to discover the history of Paris.
During the reign of Louis XV it was first a coaching inn tucked inside the ancient city walls of Paris; under Napoleon III it was a family home and then, during the Belle Époque, a hotel and the haunt of the artists of Montparnasse.
Double room 18 square meters air conditioned with either a double bed or twin beds . Bathroom with either a shower or a bathtub.

Guest access
All hotel's services

Other things
neighborhood_overview:
The Hotel Petit Paris is ideally situated in the heart of Paris’s Latin Quarter. Both the Panthéon and Luxembourg Gardens can be reached in less than five minutes by foot. While here, be sure to explore nearby Rue Mouffetard, one of the City of Light’s oldest streets, as well as the neighboring Curie Institute, a world-renowned cancer research center.

The Hotel Petit Paris is just steps away from the famous banks of the Seine, where you can take in some of Paris’s most extraordinary panoramic views, including Île de la Cité, the Louvre, and many more. Looking for a specific monument? Take advantage of the expertise of our concierge during your stay at the Hotel Petit Paris.

Other than that, the local views are breathtaking.
Its proximity to Lisbon, the beautiful town of Cascais and close to Sintra (Unesco World Heritage), allows for a quick visit or a longer walk to enjoy the peace and tranquility of the place.

neighborhood_overview:
About the area – Mayfair
Mayfair is one of the most exclusive areas in the heart of London. It borders onto Hyde Park to the west, Oxford Street to the north, Piccadilly and Green Park to the south and Regent Street to the east.

Mayfair is perfectly located for shopping and entertainment. Famous establishments within close proximity of Mayfair House include Savile Row, Burlington Arcade, the Ritz Hotel and the West End theatre district. New and Old Bond Street, known for fine jewellery, antiques and clothing is also nearby. This is also home to Sotheby’s, one of Mayfair’s oldest and most respected auction houses.

A short his­tory: the area of May­fair was first devel­oped around 1686 and became the site for the annual May Fayre (a 15 day cel­e­bra­tion from May Day and thought to have started in the days of Edward I to mark St James Day), a com­bi­na­tion of mar­ket, enter­tain­ment and mer­ri­ment, and very pop­u­lar annual event. description:
Welcome to Vasanta, your ticket to an iconic Barcelona experience. This cheerful yellow exterior sits on an octagonal block within the visionary Eixample neighborhood grid. Each space inside features high ceilings and plenty of natural light from the tall windows. Outside, the city is ripe for exploration. Tree-lined shopping through Rambla de Catalunya. Vibrant glass and mosaic murals at Casa Batlló. Fresh seafood from Passeig de Gràcia. All these spots and more are just a short walk away. Say “bon dia” to another sunny Mediterranean stay at Vasanta.

The space
Working, relaxing, living. Our spaces have all the other essentials you need for your stay.

- Contact-free check-in
- 24/7 virtual support
- Super-fast WiFi
- Fresh towels and bathroom essentials
- Pre-cleaning before your arrival
- Cable and HDMI cord provided
- Private terrace

What’s nearby
- 2 minute walk to Alsur Café Llúria (gr
neighborhood_overview: As Barcelona’s most recognizable neighborhood, Eixample is a late 19th-century urban development known for its dazzling Art Nouveau architecture. Named the "Expansion" in Catalan, the district is characterized by its geometric grid layout and is located north of Plaça de Catalunya. Admire Modernist townhouses that line the main streets, or stop by a cozy sidewalk café to people-watch while sipping a café con leche or cortado. Don’t miss the chance to visit Casa Batlló, Casa Milà, and the unfinished Sagrada Familia, all stunning attractions designed by world-famous Catalan architect, Antoni Gaudí. With stylish boutiques, upscale eateries, and more all within walking distance, spend your days exploring everything that this unparalleled neighborhood has to offer.

description:

Located just 10 minutes from the Denfert Rochereau district, you will discover the charm of this district, its many shops and cafés but especially the must-see Catacombs.

15 minutes from the famous Montparnasse Tower in a dynamic district, you can walk to the Palais du Luxembourg and its famous garden.

The space
This apartment of 65 m² in the spirit of a former artist's studio is located on the ground floor. There is a large living room with an open kitchen, a beautiful fireplace and a dining room. neighborhood_overview: The 14th arrondissement is a large residential area, but includes some of Paris' most famous attractions. The 14th it is the Montparnasse tower, the station and the Montparnasse cemetery. The neighbourhood, safe and trendy, one of the most popular and fastest growing at the moment, is busy with trendy cafes (Hotel du Nord, Chez Prune, Ten Belles, Le Comptoir General to name a few) and restaurants.
There are supermarkets nearby and all kinds of foodstores.

neighborhood_overview:
Unashamedly ostentatious, Belém’s waterfront monuments and vast open spaces are a tribute to Portugal’s Age of Discoveries and legendary nautical adventurers.

Fifteenth century Portugal thrived in the fields of navigation, astronomy, mapmaking and shipbuilding. Under the direction and legacy of Prince Henry the Navigator, pioneering local seafarers undertook perilous voyages of exploration; their goal: to discover—and ultimately control—the sea routes of the highly lucrative spice trade.

By the mid to late 16th century, scores of Portuguese colonies and trading posts linked the coasts of Europe, Africa, the Middle East and Asia: the Portuguese Empire had become history’s first global empire.



Visit Belém`s waterfront monuments

Prenzlauer Berg is no doubt one of the most mythical districts of the city.
It embodies Berlin’s cultural heritage from diverse historical periods, proletarian and middle-class styles of the fin-de-siècle, just as the imprint of socialism.

neighborhood_overview:
Barcelona architecture is, in reality, an attraction in itself. Just stroll around the city, especially through our neighborhood: "the Eixample", and you'll find an endless amount of fascinating buildings and unexpected treasures.

From Roman times to the Gothic period to the Catalan Art Nouveau, "modernisme," Barcelona's architecture naturally transmits the city's rich history. It speaks for eras of varying prosperity and decline, for fervent Catalan nationalism or subjugation to the central government, for Expos, Olympic Games, Cultural Forums and more.

The two most important styles of Barcelona architecture are Catalan Gothic, a medieval style, and Modernisme, a turn of the 20th century movement protagonized by Antoni Gaudí.

description:

The space
Our flat is your flat! Make yourselves feel at home and treat it like you would treat your own place and please leave it the way you found it.

Guest access

Other things to note<
neighborhood_overview: The neighbourhood is amazing. Go down Upper Street, which is also known as Supper Street to locals. You won't run out of places to eat. The coffee place next door, Sawyer & Gray is also pretty good, but we prefere Maison.

The neighbours
The people of Amadora are from a large variety of backgrounds and cultures, and you'll find people from every age possible. However, you will see there are lots of students around the city.

You'll fall in love with
If you love shopping, you'll love Dolce Vita Tejo! But Amadora is scattered with good restaurants. Try Maria Azeitona, where you can have some snacks with friends or enjoy a nice Portuguese meal.

The lifestyle
Amadora is usually lively during the day, with lots of shops and offices running during the day. Nights are calm, but there's always an open bar where you and your friends can have a few drinks!

Interesting spots
If you're a fan of comic books, go to Amadora’s International Comic Book Festival, which takes place once a year. It's a great way to meet some of the most funniest artists in the business.

neighborhood_overview:
Ladbroke Grove is renowned for its strong connections to the arts and music industries. The property is situated at the point where the exclusive and highly sought after Holland Park and Ladbroke Grove neighbourhoods meet. The annual Notting Hill Carnival takes place on Ladbroke Grove itself and the famous Portobello Market is but a mere stone's throw attracting visitors in their thousands.

This West London neighbourhood has undergone a lot of changes over the years, from factory housing in the 1800s to a bohemian artist paradise in the 1960s. The British Underground scene grew up in neighbouring Notting Hill, and legendary rock star Jimmy Hendrix died here. However, this is still in the borough of Kensington and Chelsea, so it was only a matter of time before the wealthy families and media moguls moved in. Amidst the posh boutiques there are plenty of cool, creative places to check out here.

neighborhood_overview:
We honestly believe it when we say that we think this is the perfect location.

The South Bank is probably London's #1 destination, and no visit to London is complete without a walk along the River.

Our neighbourhood is clearly 'on-the-up', but thankfully remains quiet* and unspoiled. (*excepting when there are fireworks)

We're near four great food markets, including the amazing and famous Borough Market and the oh-so-hipster Maltby Street Market. For more cheap-eats, there's the Lower Marsh Market and the (yummy) Real Food Market at Royal Festival Hall. There are also lots of great restaurants and bars nearby, including a few hidden gems and some great new ones.

Top cultural offerings are nearby, including the aforementioned Royal Festival Hall, with many free events, the South Bank Centre, the Hayward Gallery, the National Theatre, the British Film Institute, the Tate Modern & Shakespeare's Globe, as well as the London Eye and the Shard.

neighborhood_overview:
Oeiras itself has several points of cultural interest and many pleasant places for sports and leisure. Besides the forts of São Bruno and São Julião da Barra that mark its coast, you will also find the fantastic Oceanic Pool. At the cultural level, Oeiras has one of the best examples of the 18th century Portuguese manor house, the Marquês de Pombal Palace.
The beach can be reached from the Oeiras Promenade, and a pedestrian underpass in its central area between the beach and the Almirante Gago Coutinho Garden. From here, Av. Miguel Bombarda serves as a connection to the train station of Santo Amaro, served by trains from the Cascais Line.

The apartment h

This renovated brewery lies in the heart of Clerkenwell - a design orientated area full of restaurants, bars, and local amenities. It has great transport links to any part of town whilst also providing a quiet place to relax at night.

The space
The flat is an 1870’s brewery conversion in the heart of Clerkenwell, London, on St.John street. It's light and airy with large windows and high ceilings throughout. There are 2 bedrooms, 1 bathroom, and a large kitchen/living room area.

The first bedroom is much like the rest of the flat, with built-in wardrobe (cleared out), double bed, desk and a large window looking onto a calm central courtyard (see photos). The second bedroom is similar, but with an even bigger window onto the courtyard and clock tower. If need be, there are towels, hairdryer, soap, shampoo etc. all at your disposal.

neighborhood_overview:

See the guidebook above for a map, but to name a few places - Smith's of Smithfield, St.John restaurant, Exmouth market, etc.

It's perfectly located if you are looking for a central flat that remains peaceful. You have the trendy east of Shoreditch and Brick Lane a short bus ride away, the more commun sites a few stops on the tube west, and the river, Tate Modern and St.Paul's a few minutes down the road south.

It's a very historic part of town with the oldest church (St. Bartholomew the Great) and hospital in London at the bottom of the road. There is also the very old meat market (Smithfield) and strong connections to the crusades next door (see The Order of St.John Museum).

neighborhood_overview:
Die Unterkünfte liegen im Bezirk Neukölln mitten im 1737 gegründeten historischen Arbeiterviertel Böhmisch-Rixdorf. In unmittelbarer Umgebung: Cafés, Bars, Einkaufsmöglichkeiten, Neuköllner Oper, Kinos, zahlreiche Galerien, Volkspark Hasenheide und Tempelhofer Feld.
In Berlin bieten sich zahlreiche Möglichkeiten, historische und moderne Kultur besuchen, sich zu erholen, das Zusammenwachsen von Ost und West intensiv und lebendig erleben. Besondere Anziehungspunkten sind der historische Stadtkern mit dem Brandenburger Tor und der Straße unter den Linden sowie dem angrenzenden Regierungsviertel, einzigartige Museen, eine traditionsreiche Industriekultur, moderne Architektur oder die städtischen Naherholungsgebiete.
Auf Wunsch gestalten wir Stadtführungen mit sachkundigen Stadtführern. Hierzu beraten wir Sie gern. Für Gruppen bis 8 Personen bieten wir Führungen für 20 Euro an, jede weitere Person 2 Euro. Die Nutzung des Berliner Nahverkehrs kostet extra.

Stuff changes fast here. Recent years have seen tons of new openings (and a few closings) around the redeveloped Market Yard. A new food market is arriving. Locals fear that SE8’s character will be lost for ever, but – for now – it sails on. The 10th Arrondissement is probably the best place to live the real Parisian life experience.
It is a centrally-located gem of a Parisian neighborhood, with diverse and inventive cuisine, excellent local bars, and some of the best boutique shopping in town.
People spill into the street from the Gare du Nord, one of the busiest rail terminals in the world, and mingle into a melting pot of old Paris, new Paris, and cultural offerings from around the world.
I's where you find two of the last covered markets in Paris as the Marché St Quentin.

During you
neighborhood_overview:
Le Marais est un quartier historique de Paris. Autrefois occupé par une population d'artisans et d'ouvriers, il est aujourd'hui tourné vers l'art et la création. On y trouve plusieurs musées, et de nombreuses boutiques de créateurs. La rénovation récente de la place de la Bastille lui apporte un nouveau dynamisme et permet aux piétons de descendre directement au bassin de l’Arsenal pour continuer leur promenade au bord de l’eau.
C’est un quartier sûr où vous aimerez flâner à la découverte des boutiques de mode et de design. Il y a de quoi également raviver les papilles avec les boutiques alimentaires : pâtissiers, chocolatiers, traiteurs, fromager, glacier, etc.
Enfin, le Marais offre un large éventail de bars et restaurants aux saveurs locales et internationales.

neighborhood_overview:
Do you want to enjoy the beautiful historical city center of Amsterdam, with its canals, pubs and museums, but also have a relaxing stay? IJburg is the place to be.

You can do your shopping at the nearby shopping centre, with two supermarkets, a bakery, butcher’s shop, fishmongers, pharmacy and local restaurants. We even have our own community store, selling products made by local artisans.

IJburg's location is not only practical, it is also beautiful as it is surrounded by water, natural parks and modern architecture. Also, it has a very nice city beach (Blijburg) with restaurants and pubs.

In the summer, you can have a swim in the lake or go to the harbor to rent a sailing boat, surf gear or a wakeboard. In the winter, if its cold enough, you can go ice skating on the canals of IJburg. Also, nature lovers can go for a run in one of the nice natural parks IJburg is surrounded with.

neighborhood_overview:
One of London’s coolest neighbourhoods, Shoreditch is popular with young, trendy, creative-types — and you certainly won’t run out of things to do here.
The neighbourhood is full of colourful street art and bustling food markets, and there is always one pop up or another (if you’re visiting in the summer, Last Days of Shoreditch puts on a great urban beach and bar) as well as the regular great spots. Great Eastern Street is constantly filling up with new restaurants and cafes and Rivington Street is a safe bet for trendy shops and bars.
For a shabby-chic pub, the Commercial Tavern is a great spot and as eccentric as you might expect from its location. Those in the know, head to St. John Bread and Wine for classic ‘nose-to-tail’ dining and a buzzy atmosphere. Check out Nightjar for a funky jazz night in a basement speakeasy, serving imaginative cocktails in all sorts of interesting drinking vessels (pewter owl pitchers and ceramic flasks are just a couple of examples).

neighborhood_overview: Eixample is Catalan for 'extension', meaning an extension of the old Barcelona city, and it is one of the most popular districts in the Catalan capital. Eixample was designed by Catalan-born architect, Ildefons Cerdà, who took traffic and sunlight (amongst many other things) into consideration when drawing up the plans of the new area. Eixample is now characterised by its octagonal blocks and its grid-like pattern, with wide streets and both commercial and residential areas. It is split into two parts, Eixample Esquerra (Left, or in Spanish, Izquierdo) and Eixample Dret (Right, or in Spanish, Derecho), and is home to one of the most famous streets in Barcelona, Passeig de Gràcia, known for its high fashion stores and trendy restaurants. The street is intersected by the long Avinguda Diagonal, which runs through the entire city. neighborhood_overview:
Santos is known for its design shops, its design and architecture schools, and for bars and clubs that attract college students and teenagers. But it's also a neighborhood of grand mansions, just like the residential Lapa district up the hill. It was here that many aristocrats and noble families lived in the 18th century, and many of their homes have now been turned into hotels and embassies (the best examples are on Rua do Sacramento à Lapa and on Rua das Janelas Verdes).
Behind Largo de Santos (Santos Square) are the narrow streets of the tiny and picturesque neighborhood of Madragoa, which, together with Alfama, was home to Lisbon's fishwives and fishing community. Today it's a neighborhood known for its traditional taverns and "petiscos" (tapas) restaurants, and for its many tiled façades.

neighborhood_overview:
Poblenou is Barcelona’s creative heart: an underrated area packed with great restaurants, bars and things to do.
Poblenou was the centre of Barcelona’s industrial revolution, and the best way to get to know it is to start at the foot of the neighbourhood: Ciutadella Park, where the touristic artery of Carrer de Pujades turns into a densely inhabited industrial estate. In the surrounding eight blocks, you’ll hardly see any signs of the textile and transport businesses that were built in the ‘Manchester of Catalonia’ in the twentieth century; instead, you come across digital marketing agencies, spectacular co-working spaces, lavish speciality coffee shops and art galleries, all set in massive industrial buildings. And just when you think you’ve stepped into a Catalan-dubbed episode of ‘Portlandia’, you reach the heart of Poblenou’s residential area, a village in itself:  Carrer de Marià Aguiló.

neighborhood_overview:
A freguesia da Pena que contém o monte de Sant’Ana é um dos mais antigos distritos históricos de Lisboa. O famoso poeta Luis de Camões morreu aqui em 1580 e em 1920 nasce também aqui Amália Rodrigues a famosa fadista portuguesa. Foi também nesta área e neste mesmo prédio que viveu Antero de Quental que tinha extensas trocas de cartas com Eça de Queiroz durante muitos anos. Este bairro calmo caracteriza-se por ter muitos palácios do século XVIII e XIX como o Palácio da Bemposta, residência da Rainha D. Catarina de Bragança, viúva do Rei Carlos II de Inglaterra no início do século XVIII.

A apenas 100 metros de distância temos o Campo Mártires da Pátria que tem um jardim com um parque de estacionamento público. Aqui é possível testemunhar uma espontânea religião de pessoas que honra a estátua de Sousa Martins, conhecido médico português, há mais de um século. Não se esqueçam de visitar o Miradouro do Torel já que estão no topo da colina para que possam admirar a parte ocidental

description:
Hanky suite è un complesso nuovo,con camere ristrutturate, climatizzate,dotate di connessione WiFi gratuita.
Provvista di TV, ciascuna camera dispone di un bagno privato.
Le camere vengono pulite giornalmente.

The space
Situato nell'animato quartiere di Trastevere, Hanky suite è un complesso nuovo, con camere totalmente ristrutturate, climatizzate, dotate di connessione WiFi gratuita. Provvista di TV a schermo piatto, ciascuna camera dispone di un bagno privato con set di cortesia, asciugacapelli e doccia con Cromoterapia. Ogni cliente potrà, inoltre, usufruire di un bollitore elettrico e rilassarsi cosí con the, tisane e caffe, e un minibar. La Hanky Suite si trova a pochi passi da piazza Santa Maria in trastevere e a 15 minuti a piedi da Campo de’ Fiori e Piazza Trilussa: piazze notissime per la vibrante vita notturna, e site a 2 km dalla stazione ferroviaria di Trastevere, con collegamenti diretti per l'aeroporto di Fiumicino.

neighborhood_overview:
Il rione Trastevere è semplicemente un incanto: arte, cultura, storia, poesia e divertimento si uniscono in un unico quartiere. Perdersi nei vicoletti tra negozi di ogni genere, taverne tipiche, monumenti e chiese con opere magnifiche non ha prezzo: è il sapore migliore della Capitale italiana.
Trastevere è il cuore di Roma: ti senti a casa quando passeggi per le sue vie....

description:
Rare opportunity to rent one of our AirBnB guest bedrooms short-long term within our large 3 bedroom penthouse flat in Broadway Market. Semi private entrance, en-suite and as private as you want it to be. Perfect for self-isolators.

The space
Hello! We are 2 musicians & actors + two Egyptian Mau cats living in a beautiful penthouse overlooking London Fields and the city skyline.

We are already full-time AirBnB hosts for our ground floor level bedrooms, but due to the pandemic we are opening up the rest of our flat which means you will have access to the entire property, including 1 huge double bedroom (with extra double sofa bed) our kitchen, living room and balcony with stunning views of the whole of London.


Please note that this is our home and although the room and entrance is very private, we will still be around upstairs!

Guest access
Full property.

During your stay
We will be living
neighborhood_overview: Where to start! We live in the heart of Hackney at Broadway Market which is equal parts tourist destination as it is hub for young creatives. Huge parks, beautiful canal walks and some of the best bars, clubs and pubs in London are all within a 10 minute walk. Columbia Road, Shoreditch and the Sunday flower market are 15 minutes walk from us, and Broadway Market itself is beautiful and exciting every single day. Obviously market day on Saturday is extra special and people flock from all over the city to spend a day there - especially at Christmas! We are also just 10 minutes walk from Hackney Empire Theatre which hosts some of London's most sought after pantomimes each year.

name: Fun, light & spacious stay in lovely Montmartre
description:
Located right on the edge of artsy Montmartre - the city's most charming district - our place is a 5 minute walk from the Sacré Coeur basilica and sensational views of Paris. This 45m2 apartment is both close to all local conveniences, shops, bars, restaurants etc and well connected with transport links for the perfect, comfortable stay in Paris.

The space
The apartment consists of one bedroom with double bed, one living room, one dining / creative room, one fully equipped kitchen and bathroom, toilet etc. The place has fun and creative decoration and plenty of light from 4 south facing windows. The bedroom sleeps 2 comfortably but an additional 2 guests can be accommodated on the sofa bed in the living room. Perfect for a couple of group of four friends looking for an affordable place to spread out in. The bathroom is large with a full sized bath, shower hook up and separate toilet.
neighborhood_overview: Montmartre is a historic, artist district where the likes of Picasso, Renoir and Van Gogh once lived. Favoured by artists for it's brilliant light being up on the highest hill in Paris, Montmartre offers some of the best views the city has to offer. The area is also very trendy with plenty of great restaurants, bars, cafes and bakeries and well connected to the rest of the city with metro lines 4, 2 and 12 on your doorstep. This area really has all the ingredients for the perfect stay in the city of lights!

We are happy to welcome you to Lisbon in this amazing apartment that will make you feel at home during your stay. This apartment is a great choice for your vacation holidays in Lisbon. Located in one of the most renowned areas of Lisbon, this apartment is at walking distance from supermarket, cafés, tram and bus stop that take you directly to Belem or to the historic centre of Lisbon. We wish you a lovely stay in this great city that is Lisbon.

The space
About your Apartment
This 80sqm self-catered apartment is located on the third floor of a residential building without elevator. You have two bedrooms, one with double bed and another with a trundle bed that can turn into a double bed upon a previous request. The second bedroom is actually an extension of the living room and has no door. The dining area as a table big enough to sit 6people and the kitchen is fully equipped with everything you need to prepare your meals. You have
neighborhood_overview:
The Neighbourhood
This apartment is a great choice for your vacation holidays in Lisbon. It’s situated in Lapa area right next to the Antique National Art Museum. Here you have a nice terrace café with river views where you can have small meals or just drinks. You have a bus stop at 5minute walk where you can take a bus to Praça da Figueira (downtown) and in a few minutes, you will be in the heart of the city. From there you can also catch another bus to Belem where you can visit several of the Portuguese Discoveries monuments and taste the famous “Pasteis de Belem”. If you prefer to go to Sintra you can take the train in Rossio Station that is at a 5minute walk from Praça da Figueira. In the apartment street, you can find small restaurants, grocery shops and an amazing Boulangerie where you can have brunch or breakfast. At 800m (10min walk) there is a supermarket where you can buy groceries.

neighborhood_overview: Eixample is Catalan for 'extension', meaning an extension of the old Barcelona city. Eixample was designed by Catalan-born urban planning visionary, Ildefons Cerdà, who took traffic and sunlight (amongst many other things) into consideration when creating the plans for this new district. Eixample is now characterised by its octagonal blocks and its grid-like pattern, with wide streets and both commercial and residential areas. It is split into two parts, Eixample Esquerra (Left, or in Spanish, Izquierdo) and Eixample Dret (Right, or in Spanish, Derecho), both of which are home to some fantastic restaurants and stores. Eixample Izquierdo is delimited by the grand, Passeig de Gràcia, a paradise for shopping and dining, and Plaça d'Espanya, where the Montjuïc Magic Fountain and one of the biggest convention centres in Barcelona can be found. neighborhood_overview:
Kerameikos/Gazi is the new 'Soho' of Athens, with most major historical sites located within a 25-minute walking radius. It is safe, urban and lively, full of
unique shops, authentic tavernas, cafes, art galleries and so-far remains un-touristic. Strolling through Kerameikos in the daytime can also be deceptively low-key. During the day many Greeks go about their day, but at night the many local bars, taverns and hotspots fill up with mainly an artistic crowd from the surrounding areas. There is a supermarket and deli at just 100 meters from the house, with fresh and organic fruits and vegetables, which also sell some hot meals to go! There is also a health food store nearby, street food, hip michelin-star restaurants and other hidden gems in this surging creative area. Around the house there are plenty of free parking spots for your car as well as the exits to the National freeways.

We are also 1 stop down on the overground or 15 minute walk from Westfield Shopping Centre in Stratford, which has all the shops you could want.

- Sacré cœur

La basilique du Sacré-Cœur, consacrée en 1919, est l'un des monuments emblématiques de Paris. Située au sommet de la butte Montmartre, elle offre une des plus belles vues panoramiques de la capitale, à 130 mètres d'altitude. De style romano-byzantin, la basilique est reconnaissable à sa couleur blanche.

- Montmartre

Montmartre est un quartier de Paris (France) dominé par la basilique du Sacré-Cœur. Depuis le xixe siècle, il a accueilli de nombreux artistes tels que Picasso ou Modigliani et est devenu le symbole d'un mode de vie bohème.

My flat is very bright and very quiet. The view on the surrounding wall of the Père Lachaise's cemetery is especially amazing ! You can hear birds singing when you wake up ! You will not have the impression to be in the middle of the city !
